介绍

Introduction

 

 

 

 

《世界历史年表》试图记录从宇宙诞生之初到今天的所有重大事件。这是一项极其雄心勃勃的计划，因为历史上发生的一切都可以被视为具有某种重要性。宇宙因果律意味着，一只蝴蝶在巴西扇动翅膀，就有可能在德克萨斯州引发一场龙卷风。任何事物都不是孤立发生的，而是其他事物的结果。事实上，对于大多数人来说，一个允许事件在真空中发生的宇宙，就像一只手拍手的声音一样难以想象。

Timeline of World History attempts to chronicle all major events from the very beginning of the universe right up to the present day. This was an extremely ambitious undertaking, as everything that has ever happened can be seen as being important in some way. The universal law of cause and effect means that a lone butterfly flapping its wings in Brazil can potentially cause a tornado in Texas. Nothing occurs in isolation, everything is a consequence of something else. In fact a universe in which events are allowed to happen in a vacuum is as inconceivable to the majority of people as the sound of one hand clapping.

大多数人对我们所处世界的历史了解都相当零散。我们把在学校学到的知识碎片，和从报纸、书籍、网络或电视上看到的零碎信息拼凑起来，拼凑出一幅历史的拼图。这幅拼图几乎完全是个人化的，而且不可避免地存在误差——有时误差甚至非常大。许多年幼的孩子认为他们的祖父母生活在一个黑白世界里，仅仅因为他们相信电视呈现的世界就是真实的。他们无法接受艺术加工，就像许多成年人无法接受12月25日直到耶稣出生320年后才被定为他的生日一样。无论他们被拿出多少事实来证明这一点。

Most people’s knowledge of the history of the world in which we live is pretty episodic. We piece together fragments learned in school with those we have read in newspapers, books or taken from the internet and television in order to form a jigsaw of the past. This jigsaw is almost completely personal to the individual, and inevitably inaccurate – sometimes drastically so. Many very young children believe that their grandparents grew up in a world of black and white simply because they believe that TV represents the world exactly as it is. They are unable to allow for poetic licence, just as a lot of adults are unable to tolerate the notion that the 25 December was not assigned as Jesus’ birthday until 320 years after his birth. No matter what facts they are presented with to prove it.

如果我们生来就具备历史意识，因而天生就对自身生命的渺小有所感悟，人类或许就不会像现在这样繁衍生息。我们的人际关系、工作以及日常生活的琐碎细节，或许会突然显得多余，甚至根本不值得在意。如果这种情况大规模地发生在人群中，那对我们这个物种来说，无疑是一场灾难。

If we were all born with an awareness of history, and therefore an innate sense of how small our own lives really are, humankind might not have prevailed as it has. Our relationships, jobs and the minutiae of ordinary life might suddenly seem superfluous, or simply not worth bothering about, and if that happened to the population en masse, it could spell disaster for our species.

当我们的一生中遭遇意想不到的、足以改变世界的重大事件——例如切尔诺贝利核事故、肯尼迪遇刺或9·11恐怖袭击——许多人都会经历一次视角上的顿悟。在伊斯兰极端分子劫持两架民航客机并撞向纽约世贸中心双子塔的那一天，许多人，包括那些并未直接受到袭击影响的人，都突然直面死亡的现实，并本能地开始重新审视自己的人生。正是通过这类重大事件，普通人才能窥见更宏大的图景——那条维系时间的纽带。

When an unexpected world-altering event happens during our lifetime – such as Chernobyl, the assassination of JFK, or the 9/11 bombings – many of us experience a sudden sharpening of perspective. On the day that Islamic extremists hijacked and crashed two commercial passenger planes into the twin towers of the World Trade Center in New York, many people, including those completely unaffected by the attacks themselves, were suddenly confronted by the reality of their mortality and felt instinctively driven to re-evaluate their lives. It is through major events like these that ordinary people are able to catch a glimpse of the bigger picture – the thread that holds time together.

世界历史年表试图按时间顺序记录世界大事。几个世纪以来，各种模式必然会演变发展。人们不禁注意到，同样的敌对、嫉妒和残酷冲突在历史长河中反复出现。基督教与伊斯兰教、白人与黑人、新教徒与天主教徒以及奴隶与压迫者之间的冲突以令人沮丧的频率反复发生，但伴随着暴力和流血，也涌现出令人惊叹的人物。亚历山大大帝究竟是怎样一个人？他英年早逝，年仅33岁，却统治着当时已知世界的大部分地区。帖木儿，又名帖木儿兰，这位14世纪伟大的蒙古帝国统帅，是一个充满魅力又矛盾重重的人物。他的人生经历与成吉思汗、圣雄甘地或马尔科姆·X等其他伟大领袖的经历有多少相似之处？

Timeline of World History attempts to chronologically document world events. Patterns inevitably evolve and develop over the centuries. One cannot help but notice the same rivalries, jealousies and brutal conflicts appearing again and again throughout the passage of time. The conflicts of Christian versus Muslim, white versus black, Protestant versus Catholic and slave versus oppressor recur with depressing frequency, but alongside the violence and bloodshed astonishing people also appear. What kind of man must Alexander the Great have been? Dead at 33, but emperor of much of the known world. Or Timur, also known as Tamberlane, the great 14th century Mongol warlord, a fascinating and contradictory figure. How much did events in his life coincide with those of other great leaders such as Ghengis Khan, Mahatma Gandhi or Malcolm X?

要想了解自己身处何方，就必须了解自己从何而来。《世界历史时间轴》将帮助读者更好地理解我们所生活的这个纷繁复杂的世界。

To know where one is, one must know where one has been. Timeline of World History will help readers to make a little more sense of the confusing world in which we live.

the Ancient World

宇宙大爆炸——公元527年

Big Bang – ad 527

 

 

公元前137亿年

13.7 billion years bc

宇宙起源于大爆炸。

The Universe begins with the Big Bang.

宇宙大爆炸加一秒

Big Bang plus 1 second

氢原子核开始形成。

Hydrogen nuclei begin to form.

宇宙大爆炸加3分钟

Big Bang plus 3 minutes

核聚变停止。

Nuclear fusion ceases.

宇宙大爆炸加上379000年

Big Bang plus 379,000 years

第一批原子形成。

The first atoms are formed.

46亿

4.6 billion

太阳和行星开始形成。

The Sun and planets begin to form.

45亿

4.5 billion

一个巨大的天体撞击地球；它的碎片形成了月球。

A large body crashes into the Earth; debris from it becomes the Moon.

40亿

4 billion

地球上会形成由水蒸气、二氧化碳和氮气组成的大气层；云就此形成。

An atmosphere consisting of water vapour, carbon dioxide and nitrogen is created on Earth; clouds form.

35亿

3.5 billion

细菌和藻类开始出现；这是原始生命最初的迹象。

Bacteria and algae begin to appear; the first signs of primeval life.

25亿

2.5 billion

需氧生物繁衍生息。

Oxygen-breathing organisms thrive.

6亿

600,000,000

最早出现的动物包括藻类、扁形虫和水母。

The first animals appear including algae, flatworms and jellyfish.

570,000,000

570,000,000

海洋中开始出现复杂的生命形式。

Complex life forms begin to appear in the oceans.

438,000,000

438,000,000

一颗陨石撞击地球可能导致全球 85% 的海洋物种灭绝。

A probable meteor impact wipes out 85% of the world’s marine species.

4亿

400,000,000

海洋生物适应陆地生活，进化成两栖动物和昆虫。

Marine creatures adapt to living on land, evolving into amphibians and insects.

2.45亿

245,000,000

一场未知事件导致约 95% 的生物死亡。

An unknown event kills around 95% of creatures.

2.1亿

210,000,000

地球上 75% 的物种已经灭绝，可能是由于陨石撞击造成的。

Seventy-five per cent of the Earth’s species are rendered extinct, possibly by a meteorite impact.

2亿

200,000,000

第一批哺乳动物进化而来。

The first mammals evolve.

65,000,000

65,000,000

一颗彗星或小行星撞击墨西哥尤卡坦半岛，导致包括恐龙在内的许多物种灭绝，并使哺乳动物得以繁荣发展。

A comet or asteroid strikes Mexico’s Yucutan Peninsula, wiping out many species, including the dinosaurs, and allowing the mammals to thrive.

4,000,000

4,000,000

南方古猿人种是最早的人类，起源于非洲。

Australopityhecines, the earliest hominids, evolve in Africa.

2,500,000

2,500,000

能人（Homo habilis，意为“熟练的人”）是人类最早的物种，他们已经开始使用石器工具。

Homo habilis (‘skilful man’), the earliest human species, is using stone tools.

1,800,000

1,800,000

直立人的大脑体积是早期物种的两倍。

Homo erectus has a brain twice the size of earlier species.

1,700,000

1,700,000

直立人来自非洲。

Homo erectus leaes Africa.

20万

200,000

第一批现代人类（智人）出现在非洲。

The first modern humans (Homo sapiens) appear in Africa.

100,000

100,000

现代人类迁徙到中东。

Modern humans migrate to the Middle East.

75,000

75,000

现代人类抵达东南亚和中国。

Modern humans arrive in South East Asia and China.

70,000

70,000

尼安德特人会使用火和先进的工具。

Neanderthal man is using fire and advanced tools.

60,000

60,000

现代人类乘船抵达新几内亚和澳大利亚。

Modern humans arrive by boat in New Guinea and Australia.

45,000

45,000

在非洲，人们正在演奏已知最古老的乐器——笛子。

In Africa, the oldest known instrument, the flute, is being played.

40,000

40,000

上一次冰河时期；智人以克罗马农人的形式来到欧洲，与尼安德特人共同生活。

The last Ice Age; Homo sapiens arrives in Europe, in the form of Cro-Magnon Man, living alongside Neanderthals.

26,000

26,000

在中欧，人们正在建造用粘土瓦片做屋顶的房屋。

In Central Europe, houses are being built with clay roofs.

18,000

18,000

第一批雕塑作品产自亚洲。

The first sculptures are made in Asia.

16,000

16,000

人类跨越白令海峡到达阿拉斯加。在俄罗斯草原上，人们用猛犸象的骨头建造房屋。

Humans cross the Bering Strait to Alaska. On the Russian Steppes, mammoth bones are used to construct dwellings.

14,000

14,000

人类抵达南美洲。

Humans arrive in South America.

12,000

12,000

日本开始出现陶瓷艺术。

Ceramic arts begin to appear in Japan.

11,500

11,500

克洛维斯文化起源于北美洲。

Clovis culture begins in North America.

10,000

10,000

农业发展始于黄河流域及中国其他地区。

Agricultural development begins in the Yellow River Valley and elsewhere in China.

8400

8400

狗正在被驯化。

Dogs are being domesticated.

8000

8000

世界人口为500万。绵羊和牛正在被驯化。

The population of the world is 5 million. Sheep and cattle are being domesticated.

7250

7250

安纳托利亚的卡塔赫尤克有 6000 人口；铜冶炼和纺织制造业正在兴起。

Catal Hüyük in Anatolia has a population of 6,000; copper smelting and textile manufacture is beginning.

7000

7000

来自安纳托利亚的农业部落向希腊及更北地区扩张。耶利哥遗址发现了有城墙的定居点遗迹。陶器制作工艺发展起来，人类开始使用金属。

Farming tribes from Anatolia spread into Greece and northwards. There is evidence of a walled settlement at Jericho. Pottery develops and man begins to use metals.

5400

5400

巴德克拉米克文化在欧洲发展起来，以农民和陶工为特色。

The Badkeramic culture of farmers and potters develops in Europe.

5000

5000

海平面上升摧毁了英国与欧洲大陆之间最后的陆路通道。

The rising sea level destroys the last land bridge between Britain and Europe.

4400

4400

马匹被驯化后用于运输和战争。

Horses are domesticated and used for transport and warfare.

4300

4300

最早的巨石墓建于西欧。

The first megalithic tombs are built in western Europe.

4236

4236

古埃及历法中的第一天。

The first date in the ancient Egyptian calendar.

4000

4000

埃及人使用帆船。加纳正在制作陶器。仰韶文化在中国蓬勃发展，以水稻种植为主。

The Egyptians use boats with sails. Pottery is being made in Ghana. The rice-farming Yang-shao culture flourishes in China.

3760

3760

犹太历的第一天。

The first date in the Jewish calendar.

3750

3750

秘鲁开始出现渔村。

Fishing villages are beginning to be established in Peru.

3500

3500

苏美尔人使用一种称为楔形文字的书写和计数方式。陶轮和窑炉发明于美索不达米亚。海达文化起源于加拿大。铜与锡结合制成青铜。

The Sumerians use a form of writing and numbering known as cuneiform. The potter’s wheel and the kiln are invented in Mesopotamia. The Haida culture begins in Canada. Copper is combined with tin to make bronze.

3200

3200

苏美尔（今伊拉克境内）是第一个文明的兴起地；它是由沿幼发拉底河和底格里斯河分布的一系列城邦组成。

The emergence of the first civilization in Sumer, in present-day Iraq; a collection of city states along the Euphrates and Tigris rivers.

3100

3100

美尼斯统一了上埃及和下埃及，建立了第一王朝。象形文字开始在埃及用于交流。

Menes unites Upper and Lower Egypt, founding the 1st dynasty. Hieroglyphics begin to be used to communicate in Egypt.

3050

3050

已知最古老的医学文献，即埃德温·史密斯纸草书，已经写成。

The oldest known medical text, known as the Edwin Smith Papyrus, is written.

3000

3000

大约在同一时期，车轮被发明；多瑙河文化开始繁荣发展；欧洲出现了湖居居民；腓尼基人在叙利亚沿海定居；埃及人发明了纸莎草；亚述和埃及文化中首次使用砖块；赫梯人迁徙到安纳托利亚；英国建立了风车山文化；印度河沿岸的新石器时代村落开始发展成为大城市；中国建立了村落生活；路易斯安那州和北美五大湖区周围形成了定居点；墨西哥、洪都拉斯和萨尔瓦多开始从事农业；骆驼被驯化；算盘开始使用；战车开始使用。

Around this time, the wheel is invented; Danubian cultures begin to flourish; lake dwellers appear in Europe; Phoenicians settle the Syrian coast; the Egyptians invent papyrus; bricks are first used in Assyrian and Egyptian cultures; the Hittites migrate into Anatolia; the Windmill Hill culture is established in Britain; neolithic villages along the Indus begin to develop into large cities; village life is established in China; settlements form in Louisiana and around the Great Lakes in North America; agriculture is being practised in Mexico, Honduras and El Salvador; the camel is domesticated; the abacus is in use; chariots are being used.

2900

2900

圣经中记载的大洪水，或称大洪水，可能就发生在这一时期前后。英国巨石阵的建造工程也于同年开始。

The Deluge, or Great Flood of the Bible, may have occurred around this date. Work begins on constructing Stonehenge in England.

2800

2800

亚马逊地区出现了农业村庄。

Farming villages are appearing in the Amazon region.

2780

2780

第一座金字塔，即阶梯金字塔，建于萨卡拉。

The first pyramid, the Step Pyramid, is constructed at Saqqara.

2750

2750

传说中的吉尔伽美什统治着苏美尔的乌鲁克。

The legendary Gilgamesh rules Uruk, Sumeria.

2700

2700

埃及统治者胡夫在吉萨建造了大金字塔。在中国，人们正在饮茶和织丝绸。

Cheops, ruler of Egypt, builds the Great Pyramid at Giza. In China, tea is being drunk and silk is being woven.

2697

2697

“黄帝”黄帝在中国掌权。

The ‘Yellow Emperor’, Huang-ti comes to power in China.

2660

2660

埃及古王国的开端。

The beginning of Egypt’s Old Kingdom.

2540

2540

吉萨大狮身人面像由哈夫拉国王建造。

The Great Sphinx of Giza is built by King Khafre.

2500

2500

钟形杯文化从荷兰延伸至法国。西班牙和巴尔干半岛之间陆路贸易路线发展起来。埃及人开始制作皇室成员的木乃伊。印度的印度河谷文明兴起。青铜技术从东方传播到欧洲。美索不达米亚建造了金字形神塔，即多层神庙。挪威的一块岩画描绘了最早的滑雪者。中国人发明了针灸。

The Beaker culture stretches from the Netherlands to France. Trade routes develop overland between Spain and the Balkans. Egyptians begin to mummify dead royals. The Indus Valley civilization of India emerges. Bronze technology spreads from the East into Europe. Ziggurats, multi-tiered temples, are built in Mesopotamia. The earliest skiers are depicted on a rock carving in Norway. The Chinese invent acupuncture.

在斯堪的纳维亚半岛，人们正在使用石器工具。在欧洲的多瑙河沿岸，人们正在耕种土壤。

Stone tools are being used in Scandinavia. Along the Danube in Europe, the soil is being tilled.

2350

2350

阿卡德的萨尔贡大帝征服了苏美尔，建立了第一个伟大的帝国。中国的尧朝。

Sargon the Great of Akkad conquers Sumeria and founds the first great empire.The Yao dynasty in China.

2300

2300

最早的彗星观测记录出现在中国。

The earliest sighting of a comet is recorded in China.

2200

2200

中国夏朝的建立。

The founding of the Hsia dynasty, in China.

2193

2193

阿卡德帝国灭亡。

The Akkadian Empire falls.

2180

2180

埃及古王国以混乱告终。

Egypt’s Old Kingdom ends in chaos.

2134

2134

有记录以来最早的日食观测。

The earliest recorded observation of a solar eclipse.

2100

2100

乌尔帝国建立。

The Empire of Ur is founded.

2080

2080

门图霍特普建立了埃及的中王国时期，一直延续到公元前1640年左右。

Mentuhotep founds Egypt’s Middle Kingdom period, until around 1640 bc.

2000

2000

北欧进入青铜时代。克里特岛上的米诺斯文明兴起。美索不达米亚的乌尔城记录了最早的月食观测。中美洲开始出现集约化农业。《吉尔伽美什史诗》大约在这一时期创作完成，它是最早的文学作品之一。南岛语族人定居于太平洋岛屿。

The Bronze Age is under way in northern Europe. Minoan civilization begins on Crete. The earliest recorded observation of a lunar eclipse, at Ur in Mesopotamia. Intensive farming begins in Mesoamerica. The Epic of Gilgamesh is written around this time, one of the earliest literary works. Austronesians settle the Pacific islands.

1960

1960

埃及入侵努比亚。

Egypt invades Nubia.

1950

1950

乌尔帝国的终结。

The end of the Empire of Ur.

1925

1925

赫梯人征服了巴比伦。

The Hittites conquer Babylon.

1830

1830

巴比伦第一王朝建立。

The first dynasty of Babylonian kings is founded.

1800

1800

法国卡纳克竖立着3000块立石。

3,000 standing stones are erected at Carnac in France.

1760

1760

中国，商朝建立。

In China, the Shang Dynasty is founded.

1730

1730

喜克索斯人在埃及建立了第十五王朝。

The Hyksos found the XVth dynasty in Egypt.

1728

1728

汉谟拉比大帝在巴比伦掌权，扩张巴比伦帝国的版图。

Hammurabi the Great comes to power in Babylon, expanding the Babylonian Empire.

1700

1700

商朝中国人发明了一种文字。

The Chinese of the Shang dynasty develop a writing script.

1600

1600

巨石阵大约在这一时期建成。迈锡尼文明在希腊南部兴起。米诺斯人使用一种名为线形文字A的字母文字。埃及人撰写了一部医学著作，详细阐述了心脏的运作机制。

Stonehenge is completed around this date. Mycenaean civilization emerges in southern Greece. The Minoans use an alphabetic script called Linear A. The Egyptians write a medical book showing the correct workings of the heart.

1570

1570

埃及新王国建立；喜克索斯人被驱逐。阿蒙神庙在卡纳克建成。

The New Kingdom in Egypt; the Hyksos are driven out. The Temple of Amun is built at Karnak.

1505

1505

哈特谢普苏特女王在埃及掌权；她委托人为自己雕刻了一尊狮身人面像。

Queen Hatshepsut comes to power in Egypt; she commissions a sculpture of herself as a sphinx.

1500

1500

埃及人发明了玻璃制造工艺，并建造了已知最早的日晷；大约在同一时期，埃及人开始使用24个字母的字母表。讲雅利安语的印欧人开始在印度定居。位于今巴基斯坦境内的哈拉帕文明走向衰落。奥尔梅克文化在墨西哥发展起来。日本的绳文时代正值鼎盛时期。

The Egyptians invent glassmaking and build the earliest known sundial; a 24 letter alphabet is being used by the Egyptians around this time. Aryan-speaking Indo-Europeans are settling in India. Harappan civilization in modern-day Pakistan declines. Olmec culture develops in Mexico. The Jomon period in Japan is at its peak.

1490

1490

图特摩斯三世统治下，埃及帝国开始扩张，疆域包括巴勒斯坦、叙利亚和努比亚。

The beginning of the expansion of the Egyptian empire, under Tutmosis III, to include Palestine, Syria and Nubia.

1450

1450

来自希腊的迈锡尼人定居在安纳托利亚、西西里岛和意大利南部；他们征服了克里特岛，终结了米诺斯文明。

Mycenaeans from Greece settle in Anatolia, Sicily and southern Italy; they conquer Crete, ending Minoan civilization.

1420

1420

阿蒙霍特普统治下的埃及迎来了黄金时代。

Egypt enjoys a golden age under Amenhotep.

1400

1400

克里特岛上的米诺斯文明首都克诺索斯毁于大火。泰尔、西顿和比布鲁斯等城市成为繁荣的贸易中心。铁器时代在印度和西亚拉开帷幕。最早的印度教圣典《吠陀经》在印度诞生。盐是一种珍贵的商品，可以用来交换葡萄酒、陶器、玻璃、锡和黄金。

Knossos, capital of the Minoan civilization on Crete, is destroyed by fire. The cities of Tyre, Sidon and Byblos are thriving centres of trade. The Iron Age has begun in India and western Asia. The Vedas, the earliest Hindu sacred writings, are created in India. Salt is a precious commodity, exchanged for wine, pottery, glass, tin and gold.

1375

1375

在苏庇路里乌玛斯的统治下，小亚细亚的赫梯帝国变得强大起来。

The Hittite Empire in Asia Minor becomes powerful, with Suppiluliumas as king.

1366

1366

亚述帝国变得强大。

The Assyrian Empire becomes powerful.

1361

1361

中国天文学家记录下了一次月食。

An eclipse of the moon is recorded by Chinese astronomers.

1353

1353

阿蒙霍特普四世引入了太阳崇拜，并采用了阿克涅哈顿这个名字。

Amenhotep IV introduces sun worship and adopts the name Aknehaton.

1319

1319

拉美西斯一世建立了埃及第十九王朝。

Ramases I founds the XIXth dynasty in Egypt.

1313

1313

拉美西斯的儿子塞提重新征服了在巴勒斯坦和叙利亚失去的埃及领土。

Ramases’ son, Seti, reconquers lost Egyptian lands in Palestine and Syria.

1304

1304

拉美西斯二世大帝在埃及掌权。

Ramases II, the Great, comes to power in Egypt.

1300

1300

摩西带领希伯来人离开埃及，前往巴勒斯坦建立以色列王国。阿布辛贝神庙的建造工程也随之开始。

Moses leads the Hebrews out of Egypt to Palestine to establish the kingdom of Israel. Work begins on the rock temples of Abu Simbel.

1298

1298

拉美西斯二世与赫梯人交战卡迭什战役；双方都宣称取得胜利。

Ramases II and the Hittites fight the Battle of Qadesh; both claim victory.

1283

1283

拉美西斯与赫梯人宣布和平。

Peace is declared between Ramases and the Hittites.

1275

1275

沙尔马内塞尔成为亚述的统治者，并扩张了其领土。

Shalmaneser becomes ruler of Assyria and extends its territory.

1232

1232

拉美西斯二世之子击败了以色列人。

Ramases II’s son defeats the Israelites.

1200

1200

起源于印欧语系的原始凯尔特人开始在中欧定居。以色列进入士师时代。中国商朝时期动荡不安。奥尔梅克文明在中美洲达到鼎盛时期——在圣洛伦索建造了金字塔、神庙和宫殿组成的建筑群。

Proto-Celtic people of Indo-European origin start to settle in Central Europe.The Period of the Judges begins in Israel. There is turmoil in Shang Dynasty China. The Olmec civilization is at its peak in Central America – a complex of pyramids, temples and palaces is built at San Lorenzo.

说多利安语的希腊人定居在希腊伯罗奔尼撒半岛。亚述国王图库尔提·尼努尔塔击败了巴比伦人。奥尔梅克人雕刻了巨大的石像。中国的商朝陷入动荡。

Dorian-speaking Greeks are settling on the Peloponnese in Greece. King Tukulti-Ninurta of Assyria defeats the Babylonians. The Olmec sculpt massive stone heads. The Shang dynasty in China is in turmoil.

1190

1190

经过长期围攻，特洛伊城被迈锡尼人摧毁。

Troy is destroyed by the Mycenaeans after a long siege.

1188

1188

拉美西斯三世成为埃及统治者。

Ramases III becomes ruler of Egypt.

1180

1180

赫梯帝国大约在此时灭亡。

The Hittite Empire ends around this time.

1175

1175

非利士人、希腊人、撒丁岛人和西西里人联合起来入侵埃及；他们被拉美西斯三世击败。

The Philistines, Greeks, Sardinians and Sicilians join together to invade Egypt; they are defeated by Ramases III.

1174

1174

以色列十二支派同意互相扶持。

The Twelve Tribes of Israel agree to support each other.

1173

1173

巴比伦被埃兰人攻陷。

Babylon is sacked by the Elamites.

1170

1170

腓尼基城市，特别是推罗，变得强大起来。

Phoenician cities, Tyre in particular, become powerful.

1150

1150

迈锡尼文明开始衰落。

Mycenaean civilization begins to decline.

1140

1140

腓尼基人在北非的第一个殖民地建立于乌提卡，即今天的突尼斯境内。

The first Phoenician colony in North Africa is founded at Utica, in modern-day Tunisia.

1125

1125

尼布甲尼撒一世是巴比伦国王。

Nebuchedrazzar I is king of Babylon.

1116

1116

提格拉特帕拉沙尔一世在亚述掌权，并征服了巴比伦。

Tiglathpileser I comes to power in Assyria and conquers Babylon.

1111

1111

武王在中国建立周朝，确立了封建制度。

Emperor Wu Wang founds the Chou Dynasty in China, establishing a feudal system.

1100

1100

印欧人——其中包括拉丁人、萨宾人和萨姆尼特人——从北方迁徙到意大利。来自叙利亚中部的阿拉米人入侵亚述和巴比伦，摧毁了这两个国家。美洲的奥尔梅克人制造橡胶球用于球类运动。南美洲安第斯山脉的查文德万塔尔人建造了一座大型神庙。南岛语族在汤加和萨摩亚定居。

Indo-Europeans – among them the Latin, Sabine and Samnite tribes – are arriving in Italy from the north. Aramaeans from central Syria invade Assyria and Babylon, destroying both. The Olmec in the Americas are manufacturing rubber balls for ball games. The Andean Chavín de Huántar people of South America construct a large temple. Austronesians settle in Tonga and Samoa.

1072

1072

埃及拉美西斯十一世的去世标志着新王国的终结。斯门德斯成为法老，建立了第二十一王朝。

The death of Ramases XI in Egypt brings the New Kingdom to an end. Smendes becomes Pharaoh, founding the XXIst Dynasty.

1050

1050

撒母耳成为以色列王；以色列被非利士人征服。

Samuel becomes king of Israel; Israel is conquered by the Philistines.

1045

1045

商朝被周朝取代。

The Shang dynasty is replaced by the Zhou dynasty.

1025

1025

扫罗成为以色列王，并领导了一场成功的反抗非利士人的起义。

Saul becomes king of Israel and leads a successful rebellion against the Philistines.

1000

1000

世界人口为5000万。大约在同一时期：在意大利，原始伊特鲁里亚人在阿尔诺河和台伯河之间建立城邦；希腊人殖民小亚细亚部分地区并开始使用铁器；印欧人从中亚迁徙到伊朗；扫罗在吉尔博亚战役中阵亡，大卫继位成为以色列国王，他攻占耶路撒冷并将其定为首都；宗教经典《梨俱吠陀》在印度编纂完成；在印度北部，一些地方王国开始形成；周朝统治中国中原王国；平托印第安人在加利福尼亚建立定居点；科奇斯文化在今天的新墨西哥州和亚利桑那州一带蓬勃发展。

The population of the world is 50 million. Around this date: In Italy, Proto-Etruscans build city states between the rivers Arno and Tiber; Greeks colonize parts of Asia Minor and start to use iron; Indo-Europeans migrate from Central Asia to Iran; Saul dies in the Battle of Gilboa and is succeeded by David as king of Israel, who captures Jerusalem and makes it his capital; the religious text, the Rig Veda is compiled in India; in northern India, regional kingdoms are being created; Zhou kings rule the Central Kingdom in China; Pinto Indians establish settlements in California; Cochise culture flourishes in the modern-day area of New Mexico and Arizona.

961

961

大卫去世，他的儿子所罗门继位。奥尔梅克人发明了玉米饼。

David dies and is succeeded by his son, Solomon. The Olmec invent the tortilla.

935

935

阿苏丹二世复兴了亚述，重新确立了其古老的疆界。

Assudan II revives Assyria, re-establishing its ancient boundaries.

922

922

所罗门王后由其子罗波安继承王位，但耶罗波安反叛他，王国分裂为犹大和以色列。

Solomon is succeeded by his son Rehoboam but Jeroboam rebels against him; the kingdom is split into Judah and Israel.

900

900

在意大利，伊特鲁里亚文化传播到今天的托斯卡纳、拉齐奥和翁布里亚地区。希腊商人优卑亚人定居在意大利南部西海岸。位于墨西哥的奥尔梅克都城被摧毁，取而代之的是拉文塔的新建筑群。

In Italy, Etruscan culture spreads to modern-day Tuscany, Latium and Umbria. The Euboeans, Greek traders, settle on the west coast of southern Italy. The Olmec capital in Mexico is destroyed and a new complex at La Venta takes over.

885

885

斯巴达的莱库古制定法律和制度。

Lycurgus of Sparta creates laws and institutions.

876

876

在亚述纳西帕尔二世的统治下，亚述再次成为美索不达米亚的强国。

Assyria, under Ashurnasipal II, once again becomes a great power in Mesopotamia.

850

850

大约在这个时期，荷马创作了他的史诗《伊利亚特》和《奥德赛》。

Around this time, Homer writes his epic poems, the Iliad and the Odyssey.

842

842

以色列士兵耶户在以色列建立了一个新的王朝。

An Israelite soldier, Jehu, founds a new dynasty in Israel.

814

814

迦太基城是由腓尼基人在北非建立的。

The city of Carthage is founded by the Phoenicians in North Africa.

800

800

凯尔特人抵达英格兰。阿波罗在希腊德尔斐受到崇拜。

The Celts arrive in England. Apollo is worshipped at Delphi in Greece.

783

783

耶罗波安二世统治时期，以色列进入繁荣时期。

Jeroboam II presides over a period of prosperity in Israel.

776

776

有记录以来希腊首次举办奥运会的日期。

The first recorded date for the Olympic Games in Greece.

770

770

在中国，游牧民族袭击周朝；中国分裂为东周和西周两大王国。

In China, nomads attack the Zhou; China is divided into the Eastern Zhou and Western Zhou kingdoms.

753

753

传统上认为罗马是由罗穆卢斯和雷穆斯建立的。

The traditional date for the founding of Rome by Romulus and Remus.

750

750

迦太基是西地中海的贸易中心。斯基泰骑兵席卷克里米亚、第聂伯河和多瑙河地区。努比亚的库什王国征服埃及，统治了100年。

Carthage is a trade hub for the western Mediterranean. Scythian horsemen sweep into the Crimea, the Dnieper and the Danube regions. The Nubian kingdom of Kush conquers Egypt, ruling for 100 years.

732

732

大马士革城邦被亚述人征服。

The city state of Damascus is conquered by the Assyrians.

721

721

以色列被亚述征服；犹太人被流放。埃塞俄比亚国王在第二十五王朝统治埃及。

Israel falls to Assyria; the Jews are exiled. Ethiopian kings rule Egypt in the XXVth Dynasty.

710

710

亚述人摧毁了位于底格里斯河和幼发拉底河河口附近的迦勒底王国。

The Assyrians destroy the kingdom of Chaldea, situated around the estuaries of the Tigris and Euphrates rivers.

700

700

玛雅文明发展起来。大约在同一时期，中国陷入春秋两派的权力斗争。铁剑在欧洲变得更加普遍。

Mayan civilization develops. Around this time, China is torn by a power struggle between the Spring and Autumn states. Iron swords become more common in Europe.

689

689

亚述军队摧毁了巴比伦城，并将该遗址淹没。

The Assyrian army destroys Babylon and floods the site.

683

683

雅典结束了世袭君主制。

Athens ends its hereditary monarchy.

682

682

犹大被亚述人攻陷。

Judah falls to the Assyrians.

663

663

亚述巴尼拔的亚述军队攻陷埃及底比斯，并将努比亚人驱逐出去。

Assurbanipal’s Assyrian army sacks Thebes in Egypt and drives out the Nubians.

650

650

斯巴达在第二次墨西拿战争中击败墨西拿。

Sparta defeats Messina in the Second Messenian war.

647

647

亚述人在伊朗击败了埃兰人。

The Assyrians defeat the Elamites in Iran.

626

626

迦勒底将军那波帕拉萨尔成为巴比伦国王，并宣布脱离亚述独立，建立了迦勒底帝国或新巴比伦帝国。

The Chaldean general, Nabopolassar, becomes king of Babylon and declares independence from Assyria, founding the Chaldean or Neo-Babylonian Empire.

621

621

雅典的第一部成文法是由德拉贡颁布的。

Athens’ first written laws are introduced by Dracon.

616

616

伊特鲁里亚人塔奎努斯·普里斯库斯成为罗马国王。

The Etruscan, Tarquinus Priscus, becomes king of Rome.

609

609

亚述帝国的终结。

The end of the Assyrian Empire.

608

608

在米吉多战役中，埃及国王尼科击败并杀死了犹大王约西亚。

In the Battle of Megiddo, Necho of Egypt defeats and kills Josiah, king of Judah.

605

605

尼布甲尼撒二世（大帝）成为巴比伦王，并在叙利亚的迦基米什击败尼科。犹大从此落入巴比伦统治之下。

Nebuchadrezzar II, the Great, becomes king of Babylon and beats Necho at Carchemish in Syria. Judah comes under Babylonian rule.

600

600

奥尔梅克文明走向衰落。中国天文学家绘制了一幅星图，上面显示了1460颗恒星。

Olmec culture goes into decline. Chinese astronomers create a star map showing 1,460 stars.

594

594

“民主之父”梭伦成为雅典的唯一统治者，并改革了法律。

Solon, the ‘father of democracy’ becomes sole ruler of Athens, reforming the laws.

587

587

巴比伦国王尼布甲尼撒二世攻陷耶路撒冷，并将犹大人民囚禁在巴比伦。

The Babylonian king, Nebuchadrezzar II, sacks Jerusalem and takes the people of Judah prisoner in Babylon.

580

580

尼布甲尼撒二世开始建造巴比伦空中花园，这是世界七大奇迹之一。

Nebuchadrezzar begins the construction of the Hanging Gardens of Babylon, one of the Seven Wonders of the World.

563

563

悉达多·乔达摩王子，即佛陀，诞生了。

Prince Siddharta Gautama, the Buddha, is born.

559

559

居鲁士大帝建立了波斯帝国。

Cyrus the Great founds the Persian Empire.

551

551

孔子——中国哲学家诞生了。

K’ung Fu-tzu – Confucius – the Chinese philosopher is born.

546

546

在萨迪斯战役中，吕底亚的末代国王克罗伊斯被居鲁士击败；波斯人占领了小亚细亚。

In the Battle of Sardis, Croesus, the last king of Lydia, is defeated by Cyrus; the Persians overrun Asia Minor.

539

539

希腊人击败迦太基人。居鲁士征服巴比伦；犹大和腓尼基成为波斯的行省。

The Greeks defeat the Carthaginians. Cyrus conquers Babylon; Judah and Phoenicia become Persian provinces.

534

534

塔奎尼乌斯·苏佩布斯成为罗马的末代国王。

Tarquinius Superbus becomes the last king of Rome.

530

530

冈比西斯成为波斯的统治者。

Cambyses becomes ruler of Persia.

525

525

冈比西斯征服埃及。

Cambyses conquers Egypt.

522

522

大流士一世成为波斯的统治者；波斯帝国被划分为 20 个总督辖区，即 20 个省。

Darius I becomes ruler of Persia; the Persian Empire is divided into 20 satrapies, or provinces.

520

520

印度西北部被波斯征服。

North-western India is conquered by Persia.

510

510

在罗马，塔奎尼乌斯·苏佩巴斯被推翻。

In Rome, Tarquinius Superbus is overthrown.

509

509

罗马人将伊特鲁里亚人逐出罗马，建立了罗马共和国。

The Romans drive the Etruscans out of Rome and establish the Roman Republic.

508

508

克里斯提尼将民主制度引入雅典。伊特鲁里亚统治者拉尔斯·波尔塞纳进攻罗马。罗马与迦太基签订条约。

Cleisthenes introduces democracy to Athens. The Etruscan ruler, Lars Porsena, attacks Rome. Rome signs a treaty with Carthage.

500

500

世界人口为1亿。大约在同一时期：班图语族在东非传播；阿德纳社会在北美东部建造土墩墓葬。

The population of the world is 100 million. Around this time: Bantu-speaking peoples are spreading in East Africa; the Adena society is creating earthen burial mounds in the eastern part of North America.

499

499

在雅典的支持下，爱奥尼亚人奋起反抗波斯统治者。

The Ionians, supported by Athens, rise up against their Persian rulers.

496

496

罗马人在雷吉卢斯湖战役中击败了拉丁人。

The Romans defeat the Latins in battle at Lake Regillus.

494

494

在罗马，平民起义，从贵族手中夺取了政治权利。大流士攻陷米利都，结束了爱奥尼亚人的起义。

In Rome the plebeians revolt and gain political rights from the patricians. Darius sacks Miletus, ending the Ionian revolt.

493

493

罗马与拉丁联盟的其他国家签订条约；他们互相保证支持对抗伊特鲁里亚人。

Rome signs a treaty with the other countries of the Latin League confederation; they guarantee each other support against the Etruscans.

492

492

马多尼乌斯率领波斯军队首次远征雅典，但一场风暴摧毁了他的舰队。

Mardonius leads the first Persian expedition against Athens but a storm destroys his fleet.

490

490

第二次波斯远征军在马拉松战役中被雅典人击败。

The second Persian expedition is defeated by the Athenians at the Battle of Marathon.

486

486

波斯国王薛西斯一世发动第三次波斯远征，希腊人在温泉关战役中战败；希腊舰队在萨拉米斯海战中击败波斯人。

Xerxes I of Persia launches the third Persian expedition, and the Greeks are defeated at Thermopylae; the Greek fleet defeats the Persians at the Battle of Salamis.

480

480

欧洲凯尔特人开始迁徙到不列颠。希腊自然哲学家俄诺皮德斯测量了地球自转轴的倾斜角度。

European Celts begin to migrate to Britain. The Greek natural philosopher, Oenopides measures the tilt of the Earth’s axis of rotation.

479

479

在普拉提亚战役中，希腊军队击败了波斯军队；波斯舰队在米卡勒被摧毁，入侵结束。

In the Battle of Plataea, the Greek army defeats the Persian army; the Persian fleet is destroyed at Mycale and the invasion ends.

470

470

迦太基统治者汉诺沿非洲海岸航行至喀麦隆。

Hanno, ruler of Carthage, sails down the African coast as far as Cameroon.

460

460

雅典开启了“伯里克利时代”，这是一个黄金时代，艺术和文学蓬勃发展，许多重要建筑拔地而起。第一次伯罗奔尼撒战争爆发，雅典与斯巴达交战（持续至公元前451年）。埃及爆发反抗波斯统治的起义。

The ‘Age of Pericles’ begins in Athens; a golden age including the promotion of arts and literature and the construction of important buildings. The First Peloponnesian War between Athens and Sparta breaks out (until 451).The Egyptians rebel against Persian rule.

450

450

第一位历史学家希罗多德访问埃及。刻有罗马法律的十二铜表法——十二铜表法——被制作出来。儒家思想在中国学者中广受欢迎。

Herodotus, the first historian, visits Egypt. The Twelve Tables – wooden tables on which the laws of Rome are written – are created. Confucianism gains popularity among Chinese scholars.

449

449

斯巴达和雅典为了争夺德尔斐神谕的控制权而开战。

Sparta and Athens wage war over who should control the Oracle at Delphi.

447

447

帕特农神庙开始建造，于公元432年竣工。

Work starts on the construction of the Parthenon, completed 432.

446

446

斯巴达和雅典结束了三十年和平。

Sparta and Athens conclude the Thirty Years’ Peace.

445

445

尼希米重建耶路撒冷的城墙。

Nehemiah rebuilds the walls of Jerusalem.

440

440

在罗马，平民赢得了与贵族通婚的权利。

In Rome, plebeians win the right to marry patricians.

431

431

第二次伯罗奔尼撒战争（至公元前 421 年）。

The Second Peloponnesian War (until 421).

430

430

雅典爆发瘟疫。希罗狄奥图斯完成了《历史》。

Plague breaks out in Athens. Herodiotus completes The Histories.

429

429

伯里克利死于瘟疫。雅典卫城竣工。柏拉图出生。

Pericles dies of plague. The Acropolis is completed. Plato is born.

424

424

波斯国王薛西斯二世被刺杀；大流士二世继位。

Xerxes II of Persia is assassinated; he is succeeded by Darius II.

421

421

《尼西亚斯和约》结束了雅典和斯巴达之间的战争。

The Peace of Nicias ends fighting between Athens and Sparta.

415

415

雅典和斯巴达再次开战。

Athens and Sparta go to war again.

411

411

在雅典，“五千人政府”夺取了政权，但民主很快得以重建。

In Athens, the ‘Government of the 5,000’ seizes power, but democracy is quickly re-established.

409

409

迦太基入侵西西里岛。

Carthage invades Sicily.

407

407

雅典将军阿尔西比亚德斯平定了附属国的叛乱。

Athenian general, Alcibiades, subdues a revolt in subject states.

406

406

雅典舰队在阿尔吉努塞海战中击败斯巴达舰队。

The Athenian fleet defeats the Spartans in the Battle of Arginusae.

405

405

斯巴达的吕山德在埃戈斯波塔米附近击败了雅典舰队。

Lysander of Sparta defeats the Athenian fleet off Aegospotami.

404

404

斯巴达人攻占雅典。雅典三十僭主政府。

The Spartans take Athens. The Government of the Thirty Tyrants in Athens.

403

403

保萨尼乌斯在雅典恢复了民主制度。中国周朝的灭亡导致了战国时期的到来。

Pausanius restores democracy in Athens. The collapse of the Zhou dynasty in China leads to the Warring States period.

400

400

在色诺芬的率领下，希腊军队在库纳克萨战役中战败；随后爆发了著名的“万人撤退”。大约在同一时期，墨西哥瓦哈卡山谷的萨波特克文明正在发展。

The Greeks, under Xenophon, are beaten at Cunaxa; the fighting ‘Retreat of the Ten Thousand’ follows. Around this time, Zapotec society is developing in the Oaxaca Valley in Mexico.

399

399

苏格拉底因异端邪说被判处死刑。

Socrates is condemned to death for heretical teaching.

395

395

雅典、底比斯、科林斯和阿尔戈斯结成联盟对抗斯巴达。斯巴达国王吕山德战死沙场。

Athens, Thebes, Corinth and Argos form a coalition against Sparta. Lysander of Sparta dies in battle.

394

394

斯巴达在科罗纳战役中击败了联军。

Sparta defeats the coalition at the Battle of Coronae.

391

391

罗马人在独裁者马库斯·福里乌斯的领导下征服了伊特鲁里亚人。

The Romans, under the dictator Marcus Furius, conquer the Etruscans.

390

390

高卢人洗劫了罗马，但未能攻占卡皮托利欧山。

The Gauls sack Rome but fail to capture the Capitol.

387

387

柏拉图在雅典创立了哲学学院。

Plato founds the Academy, a school of philosophy in Athens.

386

386

斯巴达统治者安塔尔西达斯与波斯媾和。

The Spartan ruler, Antalcidas, makes peace with Persia.

385

385

希腊哲学家德谟克利特认为，夜空中那条模糊的光带是由许多小星星组成的星团。

Greek philosopher, Democritus, claims that the indistinct band of light in the sky at night is a cluster of small stars.

384

384

希腊哲学家亚里士多德的诞辰。

The birth of the Greek philosopher Aristotle.

380

380

埃及最后一个本土王朝，即第三十一个王朝的开始。

The beginning of the last native Egyptian dynasty, the XXXth.

371

371

底比斯为了对抗斯巴达而组建了雅典联盟。

The Athenian League is formed by Thebes to combat Sparta.

370

370

雅典联盟与斯巴达缔结和平。

The Athenian League and Sparta make peace.

366

366

第一次平民会议在罗马举行。

The first plebeian council is elected in Rome.

359

359

腓力二世成为马其顿国王。

Philip II becomes king of Macedonia.

355

355

第三次神圣战争始于福基斯人攻占德尔斐。马其顿与雅典开战。亚历山大大帝诞生。

The Third Sacred War begins when the Phocians seize Delphi. Macedonia goes to war with Athens. Alexander the Great is born.

346

346

雅典政治家菲洛克拉忒斯向马其顿求和。

The Athenian statesman, Philocrates, sues for peace from Macedonia.

343

343

波斯国王阿尔塔薛西斯三世征服埃及。

Artaxerxes III of Persia conquers Egypt.

339

339

第四次神圣战争爆发。马其顿的腓力二世征服希腊。

The start of the Fourth Sacred War. Philip of Macedonia conquers Greece.

336

336

马其顿国王腓力二世被刺杀；他的儿子亚历山大三世（大帝）继位。

Philip of Macedonia is assassinated; he is succeeded by his son, Alexander III, the Great.

334

334

亚历山大发动对波斯的战争；他在格拉尼库斯河击败了大流士三世。

The launch by Alexander of a campaign against Persia; he defeats Darius III at the River Granicus.

333

333

亚历山大在伊苏斯战役中击败大流士，攻占泰尔，结束了腓尼基帝国的统治。

Alexander defeats Darius at the Battle of Issus and captures Tyre, bringing the Phoenician Empire to a close.

332

332

亚历山大征服埃及，建立了亚历山大城。

Alexander conquers Egypt and founds the city of Alexandria.

331

331

亚历山大在高加米拉战役中击败大流士，波斯帝国就此终结。

Alexander defeats Darius at the Battle of Gaugamela, effectively bringing the Persian Empire to an end.

330

330

大流士三世被谋杀；亚历山大控制了波斯。

Darius III is murdered; Alexander takes control of Persia.

327

327

亚历山大入侵印度。

Alexander invades India.

326

326

亚历山大赢得了海达斯佩斯河战役，但当他的军队拒绝继续前进时，他便撤退了。

Alexander wins the Battle of Hydaspes but when his army refuses to advance, he retreats.

323

323

亚历山大去世；他的帝国被他的将军们瓜分。托勒密成为埃及总督。欧几里得出生。

The death of Alexander; his empire is divided among his generals. Ptolemy becomes satrap of Egypt. The birth of Euclid.

321

321

孔雀王朝由旃陀罗笈多在印度北部建立。

The Maurya Dynasty is founded in northern India by Chandragupta.

320

320

托勒密攻占耶路撒冷；利比亚成为埃及的一个省。

Ptolemy takes Jerusalem; Lybia becomes a province of Egypt.

312

312

从罗马到卡普亚的阿庇亚古道开始修建。

Construction begins of the Appian Way from Rome to Capua.

310

310

伊特鲁里亚人和萨姆尼特人进攻罗马，但被击败。

The Etruscans and Samnites attack Rome, but are defeated.

307

307

亚历山大在希腊的将军们，包括安提戈努斯和德米特里乌斯，都成为了各自领土的国王。

Alexander’s generals in Greece, among them Antigonus and Demetrius, become kings of their individual territories.

306

306

罗马与迦太基签署贸易条约。

A trade treaty is signed between Rome and Carthage.

305

305

托勒密成为埃及国王，随后被拥立为法老。塞琉古成为巴比伦国王，建立了塞琉古王朝。

Ptolemy becomes king of Egypt; he is then proclaimed Pharaoh. Seleucis becomes king of Babylon, founding the Seleucid dynasty.

304

304

罗马与敌人媾和，并获得了那不勒斯周边的领土。塞琉古放弃了对印度的主权，将500头大象赠予了旃陀罗笈多。

Rome makes peace with its enemies and gains territory around Naples. Seleucis gives up his claim on India to Chandragupta in exchange for 500 elephants.

301

301

安提戈努斯一世在与塞琉古及其盟友的战斗中阵亡；塞琉古统治叙利亚，托勒密统治巴勒斯坦。

Antigonus I dies in battle against Seleucis and his allies; Seleucis rules Syria and Ptolemy rules Palestine.

300

300

罗马和迦太基签订条约。大约在同一时期，玛雅人开始建造宏伟的金字塔；朝鲜王朝在朝鲜北部建立；中国制造出第一只风筝。

Rome and Carthage sign a treaty. Around this date, the Maya are constructing monumental pyramids; the state of Choson is founded in northern Korea; the first kite is made in China.

290

290

第三次萨姆尼特战争以罗马的胜利告终。

The Third Samnite War ends in victory for Rome.

287

287

古希腊数学家阿基米德的诞辰。

The birth of the Greek mathematician, Archimedes.

285

285

托勒密二世·费拉德尔福斯成为埃及统治者。

Ptolemy II Philadelphus becomes ruler in Egypt.

280

280

亚历山大图书馆成立。

The library at Alexandria is founded.

276

276

安提戈努斯二世·戈纳图斯成为希腊国王。

Antigonus II Gonatus becomes king of Greece.

272

272

安提戈努斯击退了伊庇鲁斯国王皮洛士的入侵。

Antigonus defeats an invasion by Pyrrhus of Epirus.

264

264

罗马与迦太基之间的第一次布匿战争结束。罗马举办了第一场角斗士比赛。

The First Punic War between Rome and Carthage ends. Rome holds its first gladiatorial games.

254

254

罗马从迦太基手中夺取了西西里岛的帕诺尔穆斯。

Rome captures Panormus in Sicily from Carthage.

250

250

希伯来圣经被翻译成希腊文。大约在同一时期，秘鲁出现了莫切文明和纳斯卡文明。

The Hebrew scriptures are translated into Greek. Around this time, Moche and Nazca societies are developing in Peru.

247

247

托勒密三世在埃及掌权。阿育王统治印度孔雀王朝，并皈依佛教。斯里兰卡统治者天爱帝须也皈依佛教。

Ptolemy III comes to power in Egypt. Ashoka rules the Maurya Empire in India; he becomes a Buddhist. Devanampiya Tissa, in power in Sri Lanka, also converts to Buddhism.

241

241

罗马与迦太基缔结和平；迦太基割让的西西里岛成为罗马的第一个行省。

Peace between Rome and Carthage; Sicily, surrendered by Carthage, becomes the first Roman province.

240

240

古希腊学者埃拉托色尼精确测量了地球的周长。

Greek scholar, Eratosthenes, accurately measures the Earth’s circumference.

238

238

迦太基开始了对西班牙的征服。

Carthage begins the conquest of Spain.

225

225

罗马在意大利的特拉蒙击败了凯尔特人。

Rome defeats the Celts at Telamon, in Italy.

223

223

安条克三世大帝成为巴比伦皇帝。

Antiochus III, the Great, becomes Emperor of Babylonia.

221

221

腓力五世在马其顿掌权。托勒密四世·菲洛帕特成为埃及统治者。在中国，秦朝建立，国名即由此而来。

Philip V comes to power in Macedonia. Ptolemy IV Philopater becomes ruler of Egypt. In China, the Ch’in Dynasty, from which the country takes its name, is founded.

218

218

第二次布匿战争爆发，迦太基将军汉尼拔率领军队翻越阿尔卑斯山，从西班牙入侵意大利。

The Second Punic War begins and Carthaginian general, Hannibal, leads his army over the Alps from Spain to invade Italy.

217

217

汉尼拔在特拉西梅诺湖畔歼灭了罗马军队。

Hannibal destroys the Roman army at Lake Trasimene.

216

216

汉尼拔在坎尼战役中获胜。

Hannibal wins at Cannae.

215

215

马其顿国王腓力二世为支持迦太基而进攻罗马，第一次马其顿战争由此爆发。罗马将军马库斯·克劳狄乌斯·马塞勒斯在诺拉战役中击败了汉尼拔。

Philip of Macedonia attacks Rome in support of Carthage, beginning the First Macedonian War. The Roman general, Marcus Claudius Marcellus, defeats Hannibal at Nola.

214

214

马塞勒斯开始从迦太基人手中夺回西西里岛。长城开始修建。

Marcellus begins the recapture of Sicily from the Carthaginians. Construction of the Great Wall of China begins.

206

206

小普布利乌斯·科尔内利乌斯·西庇阿在西班牙击败迦太基人。汉朝在中国建立。

Publius Cornelius Scipio the Younger defeats the Carthaginians in Spain. The Han Dynasty is founded in China.

205

205

《腓尼基和约》结束了第一次马其顿战争。

The Peace of Phoenice ends the First Macedonian War.

203

203

托勒密五世·伊庇法尼斯成为埃及统治者；罗塞塔石碑被雕刻出来，记录了他的登基。

Ptolemy V Epiphanes becomes ruler of Egypt; the Rosetta Stone is carved, recording his accession.

200

200

第二次马其顿战争爆发，希腊人在罗马的支持下反抗马其顿统治；马其顿国王腓力二世被迫割让希腊。大约在同一时期：罗马人发明了混凝土；秘鲁开始出现纳斯卡线条；如今亚利桑那州的霍霍坎人开始修建运河系统。

The Second Macedonian War in which the Greeks, with Roman support, rebel against Macedonian rule; Philip of Macedonia is forced to surrender Greece. Around this date: The Romans invent concrete; the Nazca lines begin to appear in Peru; the Hohokam people of modern-day Arizona begin work on a system of canals.

192

192

安条克三世在叙利亚战争中战败于罗马。

Antiochus III loses the Syrian War to Rome.

185

185

大约在此时，孔雀王朝在印度的中央政权瓦解。

Around this time, the Mauryan Empire loses central authority in India.

184

184

巽伽王朝由普沙亚尼特拉在印度建立。

The Sunga Dynasty is founded in India by Pushayanitra.

183

183

汉尼拔宁愿自杀也不愿被罗马人俘虏。

Hannibal commits suicide rather than be captured by the Romans.

181

181

托勒密六世成为埃及统治者。

Ptolemy VI becomes ruler of Egypt.

175

175

安条克四世·伊庇法尼斯成为塞琉古帝国的统治者。

Antiochus IV Epiphanes becomes ruler of the Seleucid Empire.

171

171

马其顿人在珀尔修斯的率领下进攻罗马，第三次马其顿战争由此爆发。

The Macedonians under Perseus attack Rome, beginning the Third Macedonian War.

170

170

安条克四世入侵埃及，俘虏了托勒密四世；埃及人拥立他的兄弟托勒密八世·欧厄尔盖特斯为王；安条克撤退，兄弟二人共同统治。

Antichus IV invades Egypt and captures Ptolemy IV; Egyptians proclaim his brother Ptolemy VIII Euergetes king; Antiochus withdraws and the brothers rule jointly.

168

168

罗马人在皮德纳战役中击败并俘虏了马其顿国王珀尔修斯，终结了马其顿安提柯王朝的统治。

The Romans defeat and capture King Perseus of Macedonia at the battle of Pydna, bringing an end to the Antigonid line of Macedonian kings.

167

167

塞琉古统治者安提库斯开始迫害在犹大·马加比领导下反叛的犹太人；犹太教的宗教活动得以恢复。

The Seleucid ruler, Antichus, begins the persecution of the Jews who rebel under Judas Maccabaeus; Jewish worship is restored.

160

160

犹大·马加比在与叙利亚的战斗中阵亡；他的弟弟约拿单·马加比成为犹太人的领袖。

Judas Maccabaeus is killed in battle against Syria; his younger brother, Jonathan Maccabaeus, becomes leader of the Jews.

157

157

犹太成为一个独立的公国。

Judaea becomes an independent principality.

149

149

第四次马其顿战争后，马其顿成为罗马的一个行省。

Following the Fourth Macedonian War, Macedonia becomes a Roman province.

146

146

在第三次布匿战争中，罗马摧毁了迦太基。

In the Third Punic War Rome destroys Carthage.

145

145

托勒密八世·尼奥斯·菲洛帕特在其母克利奥帕特拉二世的摄政下统治埃及；王位被托勒密八世·欧厄尔盖特斯夺取，他娶了克利奥帕特拉二世，然后又娶了她的女儿克利奥帕特拉三世。

Ptolemy VIII Neos Philopater rules Egypt under the regency of his mother, Cleopatra II; the throne is seized by Ptolemy VIII Euergetes who marries Cleopatra II and then her daughter, Cleopatra III.

143

143

西蒙·马加比成为犹太人的领袖。

Simon Maccabaeus becomes leader of the Jews.

141

141

耶路撒冷被犹太人解放，犹太王国被宣布为独立王国。

Jersualem is liberated by the Jews and Judaea is declared an independent kingdom.

140

140

武帝成为中国武将皇帝。

Wu Ti becomes Martial Emperor of China.

135

135

第一次奴隶战争中，西西里岛的罗马奴隶起义被镇压。

In the First Servile War, the revolt of Roman slaves in Sicily is crushed.

134

134

西蒙·马加比之子约翰·希尔卡努斯成为犹太的统治者。

John Hyrcanus, son of Simon Maccabaeus, becomes ruler of Judaea.

116

116

托勒密帝国分裂，导致多年动荡。

The Ptolomeic Empire is split, resulting in years of turmoil.

111

111

罗马与北非努米底亚国王朱古达之间爆发战争。

War breaks out between Rome and Jugurtha, king of Numidia, in northern Africa.

108

108

凯尔特辛布里人蹂躏高卢。中国武帝征服朝鲜。

The Celtic Cimbri ravage Gaul. Emperor Wu Ti of China conquers Choson.

106

106

盖乌斯·马略当选执政官，并被派往非洲与努米底亚作战。

Gaius Marius is elected consul and is sent to Africa to fight Numidia.

105

105

罗马人击败了尤古尔塔，并将他用锁链押往罗马。

The Romans defeat Jugurtha, and bring him to Rome in chains.

104

104

阿里斯托布鲁斯一世成为犹太国王。尤古尔塔被罗马人处决。

Aristobulus I becomes king of Judaea. Jugurtha is executed by the Romans.

103

103

第二次奴隶战争在罗马爆发，持续到公元前 99 年。阿里斯托布鲁斯去世后，亚历山大·詹纳乌斯成为犹太国王。

The Second Servile War begins in Rome, lasting until 99 bc. Alexander Jannaeus becomes King of Judaea on the death of Aristobulus.

100

100

大约在同一时期：特奥蒂瓦坎和中美洲其他地方出现了金字塔神庙；司马迁撰写了《史记》，这是一部中国历史；中国数学家开始使用负数；冰在中国首次被用于制冷。

Around this time: Pyramid temples appear in Teotihuacan and elsewhere in Mesoamerica; Sima Qian writes Records of the Historian, a history of China; Chinese mathematicians begin to use negative numbers; ice is first used for refrigeration in China.

91

91

罗马与意大利城邦之间爆发战争。罗马爆发内战；苏拉击败马略。

War between Rome and the Italian cities. Civil war breaks out in Rome; Sulla defeats Marius.

89

89

在苏拉统治下，罗马控制了意大利。所有意大利人都被授予罗马公民权。

Under Sulla, Rome gains control of Italy. All Italians are granted Roman citizenship.

88

88

在第一次米特里达梯战争中，罗马与本都国王米特里达梯四世·欧帕托尔交战。

In the First Mithridatic War, Rome fights against Mithridates IV Eupator, king of Pontus.

87

87

苏拉击败米特里达梯，征服雅典。

Sulla defeats Mithridates and conquers Athens.

83

83

第二次米特里达梯战争；罗马入侵并征服本都。中国武帝驾崩，导致中国陷入一段动荡时期。

The Second Mithridatic War; Rome invades and conquers Pontus. The death of Emperor Wu Ti in China leads to a period of disorder.

82

82

苏拉成为罗马独裁者。

Sulla becomes dictator of Rome.

78

78

苏拉之死。

The death of Sulla.

76

76

莎乐美·亚历山德拉成为犹太的统治者。

Salome Alexandra becomes ruler of Judaea.

74

74

在第三次米特里达梯战争中，米特里达梯吞并了罗马声称拥有主权的比特尼亚。

In the Third Mithridatic War, Mithridates annexes Bithnya which is claimed by Rome.

73

73

罗马将军卢修斯·利西尼乌斯·卢库鲁斯占领了本都。斯巴达克斯领导奴隶和角斗士发动了第三次奴隶战争，但最终失败。

Roman general, Lucius Licinius Lucullus, occupies Pontus. Spartacus leads an unsuccessful revolt of slaves and gladiators in the Third Servile War.

67

67

希尔卡努斯二世在犹太掌权，并与他的兄弟阿里斯托布鲁斯二世爆发内战。

Hyrcanus II comes to power in Judaea and a civil war starts with his brother, Aristobulus II.

65

65

罗马将军庞培入侵叙利亚并占领巴勒斯坦。罗马诗人贺拉斯出生。

Roman general, Pompey the Great, invades Syria and takes Palestine. The birth of the Roman poet, Horace.

63

63

庞培攻占耶路撒冷，吞并叙利亚和犹太。叙利亚国王米特里达梯六世自杀。

Pompey captures Jerusalem and annexes Syria and Judaea. Mithridates VI of Syria commits suicide.

61

61

西班牙总督盖乌斯·尤利乌斯·凯撒取得了他的第一次重要胜利。

Gaius Julius Caesar, Governor of Spain, wins his first important victories.

60

60

由庞培、克拉苏和凯撒组成的前三头同盟统治罗马。

The First Triumvirate consisting of Pompey, Crassus and Caesar rules Rome.

58

58

凯撒被任命为高卢总督。

Caesar is appointed Governor of Gaul.

55

55

凯撒征服了高卢北部，并发动了一次入侵不列颠的失败尝试。

Caesar conquers northern Gaul and stages a failed attempt to invade Britain.

54

54

凯撒第二次入侵不列颠，并且取得了更大的成功；强大的不列颠统治者卡西维劳努斯同意向罗马纳贡。

Caesar invades Britain for a second time and with more success; Cassivellaunus, a powerful British ruler, agrees to pay tribute to Rome.

53

53

克拉苏在与帕提亚人的战斗中阵亡。

Crassus dies in battle against the Parthians.

52

52

庞培成为罗马唯一的执政官。

Pompey becomes sole Consul of Rome.

维钦托列在高卢发动叛乱，但被凯撒镇压。

Vercingetorix leads a revolt in Gaul which is crushed by Caesar.

51

51

凯撒完成了对高卢的征服，并撰写了《高卢战记》。克利奥帕特拉七世和她的兄弟托勒密十三世共同统治埃及。

Caesar completes his conquest of Gaul and writes De Bello Gallico about it. Cleopatra VII and her brother Ptolemy XIII jointly rule Egypt.

50

50

庞培的支持者试图阻止凯撒返回罗马担任执政官。

Pompey’s supporters try to block Caesar’s return to take up the consulship.

49

49

元老院迫使凯撒放弃在高卢的指挥权。凯撒渡过卢比孔河进入意大利，引发内战；庞培逃往希腊。

The Senate forces Caesar to give up his command in Gaul. Caesar crosses the Rubicon into Italy, starting a civil war; Pompey flees to Greece.

48

48

凯撒在希腊法萨利亚击败庞培；庞培逃往埃及，后被谋杀。

Caesar defeats Pompey at Pharsalia in Greece; Pompey flees to Egypt and is murdered.

47

47

凯撒征服了克利奥帕特拉的敌人，她成为了他的情妇。安提帕特成为犹太行省的总督，他的儿子希律成为加利利总督。

Caesar conquers Cleopatra’s enemies and she becomes his mistress. Antipater becomes procurator of Judaea and his son, Herod, Governor of Galilee.

46

46

凯撒带着克利奥帕特拉返回罗马。他在非洲击败了庞培之子塞克斯图斯，非洲也因此成为罗马的一个行省。凯撒成为罗马的终身独裁官；他推行儒略历，在西班牙击败塞克斯图斯，并立其侄子屋大维（奥克塔维安）为继承人。

Caesar returns to Rome with Cleopatra. He defeats Pompey’s son, Sextus, in Africa which becomes a Roman province. Caesar becomes Dictator-for-Life of Rome; he introduces the Julian calendar, defeats Sextus in Spain and names his nephew Octavius (Octavian) as his heir.

44

44

凯撒遇刺身亡；马库斯·安东尼（马克·安东尼）夺取政权。

Caesar is assassinated; Marcus Antonius (Mark Anthony) seizes power.

43

43

第二执政联盟由屋大维、马克·安东尼和马库斯·雷必达组成。安东尼下令谋杀了演说家西塞罗。

The Second Triumvirate is formed by Octavian, Mark Anthony and Marcus Lepidus. Anthony orders the murder of Cicero, the orator.

42

42

在广场上为凯撒建造了一座神庙。在腓力比战役中，三巨头击败了布鲁图斯和卡西乌斯，后者自杀身亡。

A temple is erected to Caesar in the Forum. In the Battle of Philippi, the Triumvirate defeats Brutus and Cassius who commit suicide.

37

37

三头同盟续约五年。安东尼已娶屋大维的妹妹屋大维娅为妻，之后在埃及迎娶克利奥帕特拉。希律王成为犹太国王。

The Triumvirate is renewed for five years. Anthony, already married to Octavian’s sister, Octavia, marries Cleopatra in Egypt. Herod the Great becomes king of Judaea.

32

32

安东尼与屋大维娅离婚；屋大维向安东尼和克利奥帕特拉宣战。

Anthony divorces Octavia; Octavian declares war on Anthony and Cleopatra.

31

31

屋大维在阿克提姆海战中击败了安东尼和克利奥帕特拉。

Octavian defeats Anthony and Cleopatra in the naval Battle of Actium.

30

30

安东尼和克利奥帕特拉自杀；屋大维宣布埃及成为罗马的一个行省。

Anthony and Cleopatra commit suicide; Octavian proclaims Egypt a Roman province.

27

27

屋大维以奥古斯都之名被元老院授予最高权力，尽管罗马名义上仍是一个共和国。奥古斯都开始了为期两年的西班牙战役，以平息叛乱。

Octavian, under the title Augustus, is given supreme power by the Senate, although Rome is still nominally a republic. Augustus begins a two-year campaign in Spain to quell rebellion.

23

23

奥古斯都采用了“王子”（princeps）这一非正式称号，意为共和国的首领。

Augustus adopts the unofficial title of princeps, chief of the republic.

15

15

罗马帝国的疆域延伸至多瑙河上游。

The Roman Empire is extended to the Upper Danube.

12

12

奥古斯都的继子提比略·克劳狄斯·尼禄·凯撒镇压了潘诺尼亚的叛乱。

Augustus’s stepson, Tiberius Claudius Nero Caesar, crushes revolt in Pannonia.

10

10

大约在同一时期，死海古卷被制作出来。

Around this time, the Dead Sea Scrolls are produced.

8

8

罗马诗人维吉尔和贺拉斯之死。

The deaths of the Roman poets Virgil and Horace.

5

5

耶稣（拿撒勒人）可能出生于伯利恒的年份。

The probable year of birth of Jesus of Nazareth at Bethlehem.

4

4

希律王去世。他的王国被他的儿子们瓜分。

The death of Herod the Great. His kingdom is split between his sons.

广告 1

ad 1

世界人口为2亿。根据狄奥尼修斯·埃克西古斯于公元525年制定的公元纪年法，耶稣诞生。奥维德创作了史诗《变形记》。大约在同一时期：位于危地马拉北部的早期玛雅古城埃尔米拉多尔达到鼎盛时期。墨西哥谷的特奥蒂瓦坎人口超过4万。

The population of the world is 200 million. Jesus is born, according to the Anno Domini era created by Dionysius Exiguus in 525. Ovid writes the poem Metamorphoses. Around this date: The great early Mayan city El Mirador, in northern Guatemala, is at its height. Teotihuacan in the Valley of Mexico has a population of more than 40,000.

2

2

中国首次人口普查显示，全国人口为5700万。

The first census in China shows a population of 57 million.

4

4

凯撒·奥古斯都召提比略到罗马，并立他为继承人和未来的皇帝。《埃利亚·森提亚法》规范了罗马帝国境内奴隶的解放。大马士革的尼古拉斯撰写了14卷本的《世界史》。

Caesar Augustus summons Tiberius to Rome, and names him his heir and future emperor. The Lex Aelia Sentia regulates the manumission, or liberation, of slaves in the Roman Empire. Nicholas of Damascus writes a 14-volume History of the World.

5

5

罗马承认卡图维劳尼人的国王辛白林为不列颠国王。

Rome acknowledges Cymbeline, king of the Catuvellauni, as king of Britain.

6

6

根据当年居里纽斯的人口普查，拿撒勒人耶稣最晚可能的出生年份是……。奋锐党运动在犹太地区兴起，其成员视上帝为他们唯一的主宰。

The latest possible year of birth of Jesus of Nazareth, based on the Quirinius census in that year. The Zealot movement develops in Judaea, the members of which regard God as their only master.

7

7

斯特拉波撰写了《地理志》（有人认为大约写于公元 18 年），这部著作涵盖了奥古斯都皇帝时期罗马人和希腊人所知的世界；这是古代世界唯一流传至今的此类书籍。

Strabo writes Geographia (some claim around AD 18), a work covering the world known to the Romans and Greeks at the time of Emperor Augustus; the only such book to survive from the ancient world.

8

8

罗马诗人奥维德被驱逐出罗马，流放到黑海。中国发明了造纸术，最初用于军队。

The Roman poet, Ovid, is banished from Rome and exiled to the Black Sea. The invention of paper in China; it is first used by the army.

9

9

王莽称帝，终结汉朝，建立新朝。

Wang Mang becomes Emperor of China, ending the Han dynasty and founding the Hsin dynasty.

10

10

圣彼得的诞生，他是耶稣的门徒之一，也是第一任教皇。

The birth of St Peter, one of Jesus’ disciples and the first pope.

14

14

罗马皇帝奥古斯都去世；提比略继位为皇帝。

The death of the Roman Emperor, Augustus; Tiberius becomes emperor.

17

17

罗马历史学家李维去世。努米底亚领袖塔克法里纳斯领导了一场反对罗马政府在北非统治的起义。

The death of Livy, Roman historian. Tacfarinas, the Numidian leader, leads a revolt against Roman government in North Africa.

18

18

奥维德去世。该亚法成为耶路撒冷的大祭司。

The death of Ovid. Caiaphas becomes high priest in Jerusalem.

25

25

耶稣受施洗约翰的洗礼。汉朝在中国复辟。

The baptism of Jesus by John the Baptist. The Han dynasty is restored in China.

26

26

本丢·彼拉多被任命为犹太行省总督。

Pontius Pilate is appointed Prefect of Judaea.

29

29

施洗约翰被希律王安提帕斩首，或许是莎乐美一时兴起，但更有可能是出于政治原因。

John the Baptist is beheaded by King Herod Antipas, perhaps at the whim of Salomé, but more likely for political reasons.

30

30

登山宝训（据一些人说是3月29日，但也有人认为可能是27或28日）。耶稣于3月29日（棕枝主日）荣进耶路撒冷。据称，耶稣的门徒犹大·伊斯卡里奥特自杀。耶稣被钉十字架（日期有多种说法，但也有人认为他死于公元33年4月3日）。圣彼得教宗任期可能开始（至公元64年）。

The Sermon on the Mount (according to some, although 27 or 28 are also thought possible). The Triumphal Entry of Jesus into Jerusalem on Sunday, March 29 (Palm Sunday). Judas Iscariot, disciple of Jesus, reportedly commits suicide. The crucifixion of Jesus (suggested date, but it is also suggested that he died on April 3, 33). The probable beginning of the pontificate of St Peter (until 64).

32

32

大数城的扫罗（保罗）皈依基督教。

The conversion to Christianity of Saul (Paul) of Tarsus.

33

33

罗马遭遇金融危机，许多贵族家庭因此破产。

A financial crisis hits Rome; many aristocratic families are ruined.

37

37

卡利古拉成为罗马皇帝。

Caligula becomes Emperor of Rome.

39

39

征氏姐妹在越南建立了一个短暂的自治国家。

The Trung sisters establish a short-lived autonomous state in Vietnam.

40

40

毛里塔尼亚（今摩洛哥和阿尔及利亚西北部）被罗马吞并。

Mauretania – modern-day Morocco and north-western Algeria – is annexed by Rome.

41

41

卡利古拉被他的禁卫军刺杀。克劳狄乌斯成为皇帝。耶稣的门徒第一次被称为基督徒。

Caligula is assassinated by his Praetorian Guards. Claudius becomes emperor. The disciples of Jesus are called Christians for the first time.

43

43

罗马皇帝克劳狄乌斯入侵不列颠；罗马人建立了伦敦（当时称为伦迪尼姆）和彼得伯​​勒两座城市，并开始修建一条后来被称为埃尔明街的道路。福音传道者马可成为亚历山大第一任东正教牧首，从而在非洲建立了基督教教会。越南成为中国的一个省。

Roman Emperor Claudius invades Britain; Romans found the cities of London, then known as Londinium, and Peterborough, and begin to construct a road that later becomes Ermine Street. Mark the Evangelist becomes the first Orthodox Patriarch of Alexandria, thus establishing the Christian Church in Africa. Vietnam becomes a province of China.

46

46

人口普查显示，罗马公民超过600万。罗马人建造了第一座伦敦桥。

A census shows that there are more than 6,000,000 Roman citizens. The Romans build the first London Bridge.

48

48

拥有300年历史的中亚匈奴帝国瓦解。

The 300-year-old Central Asian Hsiung-nu Empire dissolves.

50

50

罗马皇帝克劳狄乌斯收养尼禄·克劳狄乌斯·凯撒·德鲁苏斯为子。伦敦取代科尔切斯特成为罗马行省的首府。亚历山大的希罗发明了蒸汽轮机。阿克苏姆王国在埃塞俄比亚建立。贵霜帝国控制了印度北部。大约在同一时期，佛教传入中国。纳斯卡文化在秘鲁沿海地区蓬勃发展。

Roman Emperor Claudius adopts Nero Claudius Caesar Drusus as his son. Londinium takes over from Colchester as capital of the local Roman province. Hero of Alexandria invents a steam turbine. The kingdom of Axum is founded in Ethiopia. The Kushan Empire controls the north of India. Around this date, Buddhism arrives in China. Nazca culture flourishes along the coast of Peru.

51

51

英国抵抗运动领袖卡拉塔库斯被俘并押往罗马。

Caractacus, a British resistance leader, is captured and taken to Rome.

54

54

克劳狄乌斯去世；尼禄继任罗马皇帝。

The death of Claudius; Nero succeeds him as Emperor of Rome.

55

55

使徒保罗写了《哥林多前书》。

The apostle Paul writes his First Epistle to the Corinthians.

56

56

罗马与帕提亚之间爆发战争。保罗写下《歌罗西书》第二封信（大概日期）。

War between Rome and Parthia. Paul writes his Second Epistle to the Colossians (probable date).

57

57

中国皇帝汉明帝即位。

Accession of the Chinese Emperor, Han Ming-Ti.

58

58

保罗被囚禁在凯撒利亚，他放弃了罗马公民身份，被送回罗马受审；他写下了《罗马书》。中国新皇帝明帝将佛教传入中国和西印度河流域。

Paul, imprisoned in Caesarea, revokes his Roman citizenship and is sent to Rome to be judged; he writes his Epistle to the Romans. Ming-Ti, new Emperor of China, introduces Buddhism to China and the West Indus Valley.

59

59

佩特罗尼乌斯在《萨蒂利孔》中嘲讽了罗马的道德败坏。

Petronius pokes fun at Roman immorality in the Satyricon.

60

60

布狄卡，伊塞尼女王，领导了英国反抗罗马人的起义。

Boudicca, Queen of the Iceni, leads a rebellion against the Romans in Britain.

61

61

布狄卡在沃特林街战役中战败，被罗马总督苏埃托尼乌斯·保利努斯所杀。一支罗马军队深入尼罗河谷，远至苏丹。

Boudicca is defeated in the Battle of Watling Street and killed by the Roman governor, Suetonius Paulinus. A Roman force explores the Nile Valley as far as Sudan.

62

62

地震导致卡拉布里亚多座城市受损，其中包括庞贝城。

An earthquake damages cities in Calabria, including Pompeii.

64

64

罗马大火摧毁了半座城市；据说尼禄皇帝在安全距离外弹奏里拉琴唱歌，同时观看这场大火。

The Great Fire of Rome destroys half the city; Emperor Nero allegedly plays his lyre and sings while watching the blaze from a safe distance.

66

66

哈雷彗星可见。犹太人反抗罗马人的伟大起义以耶路撒冷圣殿的毁灭而告终。

Halley’s Comet is visible. The Great Jewish Revolt against the Romans ends with the destruction of the Temple in Jerusalem.

67

67

教宗利努斯继圣伯多禄之后成为第二任教宗。使徒圣伯多禄和圣保禄可能在同一年殉道。

Pope Linus succeeds St Peter as the second pope. The apostles, Saints Peter and Paul are possibly martyred in the same year.

68

68

尼禄自杀。

Nero commits suicide.

69

69

罗马帝国爆发内战；“四帝之年”结束，韦斯帕芗登基。中国建造了一座铁链悬桥。

Civil war in the Roman Empire; the ‘Year of the Four Emperors’ ends with Vespasian in power. A bridge suspended by iron chains is built in China.

白马寺的修建标志着佛教正式传入中国。

The building of the White Horse Temple signals the official arrival of Buddhism in China.

72

72

罗马斗兽场开始动工。

Work begins on the Colosseum in Rome.

76

76

威尔士被罗马吞并。

Wales is annexed by Rome.

77

77

英格兰总督阿格里科拉将罗马的影响力扩展到了克莱德河口。一支罗马舰队探索了苏格兰北部，远至奥克尼群岛和设得兰群岛。罗马人发明了一种简单的蒸馏方法。

Agricola, Governor of England, extends Roman influence to the mouth of the Clyde. A Roman squadron explores the north of Scotland, as far as the Orkney and Shetland Islands. The Romans develop a simple method of distillation.

78

78

萨卡纪元的基准年（零年）被一些印度教历法、印度国家历法和柬埔寨佛教历法所采用。哲学家王冲（Wang Chong）认为一切现象都有其物质原因。

The base year (year zero) of the Saka era used by some Hindu calendars, the Indian national calendar, and the Cambodian Buddhist calendar. The philosopher Wang Chong (Wang-Tchoung) claims all phenomena have material causes.

79

79

提图斯继承其父韦斯帕芗成为罗马皇帝。维苏威火山爆发，摧毁了庞贝和赫库兰尼姆，造成包括作家兼哲学家老普林尼在内的许多人丧生。格奈乌斯·尤利乌斯·阿格里科拉入侵苏格兰，但遭到喀里多尼亚人的抵抗。在中国，一个学者委员会编纂了孔子及其学派的著作。

Titus succeeds his father, Vespasian, as Roman Emperor. The eruption of Mount Vesuvius destroys Pompeii and Herculaneum, killing many, including author and philosopher, Pliny the Elder. Gnaeus Julius Agricola enters Scotland but is resisted by the Caledonians. In China, a commission of scholars compiles the text of works by Confucius and his school.

80

80

罗马斗兽场竣工。罗马原万神殿毁于火灾。大约在同一时期，《路加福音》和《使徒行传》成书。

The Colosseum amphitheatre in Rome is completed. The original Pantheon in Rome is destroyed by fire. Around this date, the Gospel of Luke and Acts are written.

81

81

图密善继承其兄提图斯成为罗马皇帝。

Domitian succeeds his brother Titus as Roman Emperor.

90

90

约翰福音已经写成。

The Gospel of John is written.

96

96

《启示录》成书于（传统日期）。佛教的分裂在印度催生了一种新的、广受欢迎的宗教——大乘佛教。

The Book of Revelation is written (traditional date). A schism in Buddhism creates a new, popular religion in India, Mahâyâna (Grand Vehicle).

97

97

中国军队抵达里海。

Chinese troops reach the Caspian Sea.

98

98

图拉真是一位杰出的军事家和管理者，他是第一位来自罗马行省伊塔利卡（位于西班牙塞维利亚附近）的皇帝。

Trajan, a brilliant soldier and administrator, becomes the first emperor from a Roman province, Italica, near Seville in Spain.

99

99

用玻璃制成、背面贴有锡片的镜子取代了以前完全用金属制成的镜子。

Mirrors made of glass, backed with a tin sheet, replace previous efforts made entirely of metal.

100

100

到此时，狮子在欧洲已经灭绝。砖块成为罗马帝国的主要建筑材料。《爱经》的编纂工作在印度开始。在中国，纸张成为主要的书面交流媒介，独轮车也首次出现。位于今墨西哥境内的特奥蒂瓦坎人口达到5万。大约在同一时期：秘鲁的莫切文明开始兴起；霍普韦尔文化在密西西比河上游（今俄亥俄州附近）蓬勃发展；美国西南部莫戈隆文化发展；中国首次使用磁罗盘。

Lions are extinct in Europe by this date. Bricks become the primary building material in the Roman Empire. The compilation of the Kama Sutra begins in India. In China, paper becomes the main medium for written communication and the wheelbarrow makes its first appearance. Teotihuacan, in what is now Mexico, has a population of 50,000. Around this date: The beginnings of the Moche civilization in Peru; Hopewell culture flourishes on the upper Mississippi, around what is now Ohio; the development of Mogollon culture in the south-western United States; the first magnetic compass is used in China.

104

104

罗马诗人马提亚尔之死。

The death of the Roman poet, Martial.

109

109

基督教教会宣称自己是普世的（大公的）。

The Christian Church proclaims itself to be universal (catholic).

110

110

《约翰福音》写于小亚细亚。

The Gospel of John is written in Asia Minor.

113

113

小普林尼之死，他是罗马律师和科学家。

The death of Pliny the Younger, Roman lawyer and scientist.

115

115

昔兰尼加（利比亚东北部）的犹太社群起义反抗罗马统治。埃及的亚历山大港在犹太-希腊内战期间被摧毁。

The Jewish community in Cyrenaica (north-eastern Libya) revolts against the Roman administration. Alexandria in Egypt is destroyed during the Jewish–Greek civil wars.

117

117

图拉真皇帝之后，另一位西班牙人哈德良继位。

Emperor Trajan is succeeded by Hadrian, another Spaniard.

118

118

由图拉真下令建造的罗马广场已经竣工。

The Roman Forum, commissioned by Trajan, is finished.

120

120

哈德良皇帝访问英国，当时福斯堤道正在修建。希腊历史学家普鲁塔克逝世。贵霜国王迦腻色迦控制了印度北部和巴基斯坦的大片地区。中国张衡发明了地震仪。

Emperor Hadrian visits Britain where the Foss Dyke is being constructed. The Greek historian Plutarch dies. Kushan king, Kanishka, takes control of large areas of northern India and Pakistan. The invention of the seismograph by Zhang Heng, in China.

121

121

哈德良将罗马不列颠和喀里多尼亚之间的边界线划定在一条从泰恩河延伸到索尔威湾的线上。

Hadrian fixes the border between Roman Britain and Caledonia on a line running from the River Tyne to the Solway Firth.

122

122

为了抵御北方入侵，罗马不列颠行省开始修建哈德良长城。

Work begins on the construction of Hadrian’s Wall to defend the Roman province of Britain from invasion from the north.

123

123

在爱尔兰，穆格·努阿达特击败了爱尔兰国王康恩（百战之王）。中国科学家张衡修正了历法，使其与季节相符。

In Ireland, Mug Nuadat defeats the Irish king, Conn of the Hundred Battles. Chinese scientist, Zhang Heng, corrects the calendar to bring it into line with the seasons.

125

125

罗马万神殿的重建工作开始。

Reconstruction work begins on the Pantheon in Rome.

130

130

讽刺作家尤维纳利斯去世。巴士拉成为阿拉伯半岛的首都。

The death of the satirist, Juvenal. Basra becomes the capital of Arabia.

134

134

罗马雅典娜神学院（一所修辞学、法律和哲学大学）的开幕。

The opening of the Athenaeum, a university of rhetoric, law and philosophy in Rome.

138

138

罗马皇帝哈德良去世；安东尼·庇护继位。

The death of the Roman Emperor, Hadrian; Antoninus Pius succeeds him.

142

142

安东尼长城的建造始于苏格兰。

Construction of the Antonine Wall begins in Scotland.

150

150

特奥蒂瓦坎太阳金字塔建成，它是美洲最高的哥伦布发现美洲大陆之前的建筑。大约在同一时期，最早的地图集——托勒密的《地理志》 ——编纂完成。

The construction of the Great Pyramid of the Sun in Teotihuacan, the tallest pre-Colombian building in the Americas. Around this time, the earliest atlas, Ptolemy’s Geography, is compiled.

151

151

米蒂利尼和士麦那被地震摧毁。

Mytilene and Smyrna are destroyed by an earthquake.

155

155

罗马人开始放弃哈德良长城。

The Romans begin to abandon Hadrian’s Wall.

160

160

罗马制造了一种含有油脂、石灰和灰烬的肥皂。最早的佛教僧侣出现在中国。

In Rome, soap containing grease, lime and ashes is manufactured. The first Buddhist monks appear in China.

161

161

马可·奥勒留继安东尼·庇护之后成为皇帝。

Marcus Aurelius succeeds Antoninus Pius as Emperor.

166

166

罗马与帕提亚之间的战争结束了。瘟疫肆虐罗马帝国。

The end of the war between Rome and Parthia. Plague lays waste to the Roman Empire.

168

168

希腊天文学家和占星家托勒密的逝世。

The death of Ptolemy, Greek astronomer and astrologer.

170

170

马可·奥勒留下令在帝国境内对基督徒和奴隶实行人道待遇。

Marcus Aurelius orders humane treatment for Christians and slaves throughout the Empire.

180

180

马可·奥勒留的去世终结了被称为“罗马和平”（Pax Romana）的漫长和平时期。哥特人抵达黑海沿岸。一场旷日持久的天花疫情使罗马人口锐减。

The death of Marcus Aurelius brings an end to the long period of peace known as the Pax Romana. The Goths reach the banks of the Black Sea. A long smallpox epidemic sharply decreases the population of Rome.

181

181

新西兰陶波湖火山爆发；远在罗马和中国都能感受到其影响。

The Lake Taupo Volcano in New Zealand erupts; the effects are seen as far away as Rome and China.

184

184

在中国，黄巾军（一场农民运动）发动的叛乱削弱了汉朝。

In China, a rebellion by the Yellow Turban sect, a peasant movement, weakens the Han dynasty.

185

185

在印度，瓦苏提婆成为贵霜皇帝。中国天文学家最早观测到超新星。

In India, Vasudeva becomes Kushan Emperor. Chinese astronomers make the earliest identification of a supernova.

190

190

一条罗马大道经由辛普朗山口穿越阿尔卑斯山。克莱奥梅德斯教导说，月亮反射阳光，自身并不发光。印度南部坦焦尔附近兴起了印度教朱罗王朝。

A Roman road crosses the Alps by the Simplon Pass. Cleomedes teaches that the moon reflects sunlight and does not glow on its own. The rise of the Hindu Chola kingdom near Tanjore in southern India.

193

193

佩蒂纳克斯成为罗马皇帝，但被禁卫军刺杀，禁卫军随后将皇位拍卖给了迪迪乌斯·朱利安努斯。迪迪乌斯·朱利安努斯也遭到刺杀后，利比亚人塞普蒂米乌斯·塞维鲁继位。

Pertinax becomes Roman Emperor but is assassinated by the Praetorian Guard, who then sell the throne in an auction to Didius Julianus. When he, too, is assassinated, a Lybian, Septimus Severus, takes over.

195

195

在中国，匈奴联盟越过长城，在山西省建立了政权。

In China, the Xiongnu federation crosses the Great Wall and establishes itself in Shanxi province.

197

197

罗马军队攻占并洗劫了拜占庭，并重新夺回了美索不达米亚。

Roman troops capture and sack Byzantium and retake Mesopotamia.

200

200

世界人口为2.57亿。罗马皇帝塞普蒂米乌斯·塞维鲁修建了一系列堡垒和战壕，以加强北非的边境防御。大约在同一时期，玻利维亚的的喀喀湖附近的蒂亚瓦纳科城开始进行大规模建设。

The population of the world is 257 million. Roman Emperor Septimius Severus builds a chain of forts and trenches in order to strengthen frontier defences in North Africa. Around this date, major construction begins at the city of Tiahuanaco, close to Lake Titicaca in Bolivia.

202

202

罗马法律禁止女性参加角斗士比赛。

A Roman law bans female gladiators.

210

210

罗马人在入侵苏格兰遭受惨重损失后，与苏格兰人媾和。

The Romans make peace with the Scots after suffering heavy losses invading Scotland.

211

211

罗马皇帝塞普蒂米乌斯·塞维鲁在约克去世；他的儿子卡拉卡拉和盖塔继承了他的皇位。

Roman Emperor Septimus Severus dies in York; he is succeeded by his sons, Caracalla and Geta.

212

212

罗马帝国境内所有自由出生的人都享有罗马公民权。

All free-born people within the Roman Empire are granted Roman citizenship.

220

220

哥特人入侵小亚细亚和巴尔干半岛。中国汉朝灭亡，随后是三国时期（魏、吴、蜀）和金朝。

The Goths invade Asia Minor and the Balkans. The end of the Han dynasty in China, followed by the Three Kingdoms (Wei, Wu and Shu) and the Jin dynasty.

221

221

刘备，一位中国军阀，汉朝皇室后裔，称帝称帝，蜀汉国建立。

Liu Bei, a Chinese warlord and a descendant of the royal family of the Han Dynasty, proclaims himself Emperor. The Shu Han Kingdom is established.

222

222

中国建立了吴国。

The kingdom of Wu is established in China.

224

224

大约在这一时期，帕提亚帝国在波斯帝国的统治走向终结。

Around this date, Parthian power comes to an end in the Persian Empire.

225

225

第一批基督教绘画出现在罗马，用于装饰地下墓穴。阿尔达希尔一世加冕为波斯“万王之王”，开启了萨珊王朝长达400年的统治。

The first Christian paintings appear in Rome, decorating the Catacombs. Ardashir I is crowned ‘King of Kings’ of Persia, beginning the 400-year reign of the Sassanid Empire.

226

226

在爱尔兰，科马克·麦克·艾尔特（Cormac mac Airt）大王的统治开始了。

In Ireland the rule of High King Cormac mac Airt begins.

230

230

波斯国王阿尔达希尔一世入侵罗马的美索不达米亚行省，罗马皇帝亚历山大率军东征迎战。

Ardashir I of Persia invades the Roman province of Mesopotamia and Roman Emperor Alexander travels east to fight him.

235

235

内战和混乱使罗马帝国陷入瘫痪，直到公元 284 年，26 位皇位觊觎者争夺权力。

Civil war and chaos cripple the Roman Empire until 284 as 26 claimants to the imperial throne vie for power.

238

238

奥利金用五种语言出版了《旧约》。非洲爆发反抗罗马统治的起义，由此开启了长达半个世纪的动荡。

Origenes publishes The Old Testament in five languages. Revolt in Africa against Roman rule begins a half-century of unrest.

239

239

在中国魏国，魏齐王继承了魏明帝的王位。

In the Chinese kingdom of Wei, Wei Qi Wang succeeds Wei Ming Di.

241

241

沙普尔一世继承阿尔达希尔一世成为波斯国王。

Shapur I succeeds Ardashir I as king of Persia.

242

242

罗马皇帝戈尔迪安三世撤离了博斯普鲁斯海峡的辛梅里安城市；该地区现在由东哥特人控制。

The Roman Emperor Gordian III evacuates the Cimmerian cities in the Bosphorus; the territory is now controlled by the Ostrogoths.

243

243

戈尔迪安三世在雷萨纳战役中击败波斯国王沙普尔一世。孙良成为中国吴国的皇帝。

Gordian III defeats Shapur I of Persia in the battle of Resaena. Sun Liang becomes emperor of the Chinese kingdom of Wu.

247

247

第一次哥特人入侵罗马帝国。日本爆发内战。

The first Gothic invasion of the Roman Empire takes place. Civil War begins in Japan.

249

249

德西乌斯被军队拥立为帝，在维罗纳击败并杀死了在位皇帝阿拉伯人腓力。

Decius, proclaimed emperor by the army, defeats and kills incumbent Emperor Philip the Arab at Verona.

250

250

哥特人入侵了位于今塞尔维亚和保加利亚境内的默西亚地区。玛雅文明的古典时期始于危地马拉、洪都拉斯和墨西哥东部。

The Goths invade Moesia in the areas of present-day Serbia and Bulgaria. The classic period of Mayan civilization begins in Guatemala, Honduras and eastern Mexico.

251

251

在阿布里图斯战役中，哥特人击败了罗马人；罗马的两位共同皇帝德西乌斯和赫伦尼乌斯·伊特鲁斯库斯阵亡。罗马帝国爆发了一场持续15年的瘟疫。

In the Battle of Abrittus, the Goths defeat the Romans; joint-emperors Decius and Herennius Etruscus are killed. A 15-year plague begins in the Roman Empire.

253

253

罗马帝国三十僭主时期；边境地区的将领被其军队拥立为帝。哥特人入侵小亚细亚，兵临塞萨洛尼卡城下。

The period of the Thirty Tyrants in the Roman Empire; generals in the border regions are declared emperors by their troops. The Goths invade Asia Minor and appear at the walls of Thessalonica.

256

256

法兰克人渡过莱茵河；阿拉曼尼人抵达米兰；罗马帝国境内的城市开始修建城墙，因为其边境防御开始崩溃。

The Franks cross the Rhine; the Alamanni reach Milan; cities in the Roman Empire begin to build walls as the defence of its frontiers begins to crumble.

258

258

高卢、不列颠和西班牙脱离罗马帝国，组成了高卢帝国。

Gaul, Britain and Spain separate from the Roman Empire; they form the Gallic empire.

260

260

罗马皇帝瓦勒良被波斯国王沙普尔一世击败并俘虏。南京大学在中国南京成立。

Roman Emperor Valerian is defeated and captured by Shapur I of Persia. Nanjing University is founded in Nanjing, China.

262

262

哥特人烧毁了以弗所的阿尔忒弥斯神庙原址。

The Goths burn down the original Temple of Artemis at Ephesus.

263

263

魏国征服了蜀汉国，蜀汉国是中国三大国之一。

The Wei kingdom conquers the kingdom of Shu Han, one of the Chinese Three kingdoms.

264

264

孙昊继承孙秀成为中国吴国的统治者。

Sun Hao succeeds Sun Xiu as ruler of the Chinese kingdom of Wu.

265

265

加里恩努斯与父亲瓦莱里安共同执政，击退了哥特人在巴尔干半岛的入侵。晋武帝成为晋朝的第一位皇帝。

Gallienus, Roman co-emperor with his father Valerian, repels the invasion of the Goths in the Balkans. Emperor Wu of Jin becomes the Jin dynasty’s first emperor.

267

267

哥特人发动了对罗马帝国的第一次大规模蛮族入侵。

The Goths launch one of the first major barbarian invasions of the Roman Empire.

268

268

加里恩努斯在奈苏斯战役中击败了哥特人。

Gallienus defeats the Goths at the Battle of Naissus.

269

269

在叙利亚帕尔米拉帝国女王芝诺比亚的将军扎布达斯的一次袭击中，亚历山大图书馆被烧毁。

The library at Alexandria is burned down during a raid by Zabdas, a general of Zenobia, queen of the Palmyrene Empire in Syria.

270

270

罗马帝国遭遇严重的经济危机；一些地区的通货膨胀率飙升至1000%。

A serious economic crisis strikes the Roman Empire; inflation soars to 1,000% in some areas.

271

271

罗马城周围的奥勒良城墙建成（于公元276年完工）。中国首次使用磁罗盘。

The Aurelian walls around Rome are built (finished in 276). The first use of a magnetic compass in China.

272

272

巴黎第一任主教圣丹尼斯和他的两位门徒在后来被称为蒙马特山（殉道者之山）的一座小山附近被斩首。

Saint Denis, the first bishop of Paris, and two of his disciples are beheaded near a hill later called Montmartre, the Mountain of the Martyrs.

274

274

高卢帝国被罗马皇帝奥勒良重新征服。罗马帝国再次统一。晋朝征服了中国的东吴王朝。

The Gallic empire is reconquered by Roman Emperor Aurelian. The Roman Empire is united again. The Jin dynasty conquers the Eastern Wu dynasty in China.

280

280

日耳曼部落图林根人出现。吴国被晋国灭亡，中国三国时期就此结束。

The Germanic tribe, the Thuringii, appears. The kingdom of Wu is dissolved by Jin, finally ending the Three Kingdoms period of China.

284

284

罗马皇帝戴克里先推行了重大改革，包括四帝共治制，即由四位皇帝共同统治帝国。

Diocletian, Emperor of Rome introduces major reforms including a tetrarchy; four emperors ruling the Empire together.

290

290

晋惠帝继晋武帝成为中国皇帝。

Jin Hui Di succeeds Jin Wu Di as Emperor of China.

300

300

大约在这一时期：法兰克人进入比利时北部；北非的大象灭绝；东南非洲的班图人开始放牧牛群，他们之前是谷物种植者；玛雅人创造了文字系统并制定了历法。

Around this date: The Franks penetrate northern Belgium; the elephant becomes extinct in North Africa; the Bantu in south-east Africa begin to herd cattle, having been cereal farmers; the Mayans create a system of writing and develop a calendar.

301

301

亚美尼亚成为第一个接受基督教为国教的国家。

Armenia becomes the first nation to accept Christianity as its state religion.

304

304

匈奴刘元建立了汉朝，开启了中国的十六国时代。

The Hun Liu Yuan establish the Han kingdom, beginning the Sixteen Kingdoms era in China.

305

305

伊利贝里斯会议颁布法令，规定神父必须独身。

The Council of Illiberis decrees that priests must be celibate.

306

306

基督教在英国确立了地位。始于公元291年的八亲王内战结束。

Christianity is established in Britain. The Civil War of the Eight Princes, started in 291 ends.

307

307

晋怀帝成为中国皇帝。

Jin Huai Di becomes Emperor of China.

311

311

中国首都洛阳被匈奴人攻陷，皇帝被俘。

Luoyang, capital of China, is sacked by barbarians under the leadership of the Huns; the emperor is captured.

312

312

罗马皇帝君士坦丁承认基督教为罗马国教。

The Roman Emperor Constantine acknowledges Christianity as the Roman religion.

313

313

君士坦丁颁布米兰敕令，结束了罗马帝国对基督徒的一切迫害。

Constantine issues the Edict of Milan, ending all persecution of Christians in the Roman Empire.

315

315

罗马帝国废除了十字架刑罚。君士坦丁凯旋门在罗马竣工。

Crucifixion is abolished as a punishment in the Roman Empire. The Arch of Constantine is completed in Rome.

316

316

匈奴攻陷了中国西晋王朝的都城长安。皇帝金敏帝投降，西晋王朝灭亡。

The Xiongnu sack Chang’an, capital of the Chinese Western Jin Dynasty. Jin Mindi, the emperor, surrenders, bringing the dynasty to an end.

320

320

12月25日被定为耶稣的诞辰。笈多王朝在印度恒河谷地区崛起。

December 25 is introduced as the birthday of Jesus. The Gupta empire becomes powerful in the Ganges Valley in India.

324

324

君士坦丁在克里索波利斯战役中击败利西尼乌斯，成为罗马唯一的皇帝，结束了四帝共治制。罗马的圣彼得大教堂建成。

Constantine defeats Licinius at the Battle of Chrysopolis, and becomes sole Emperor of Rome, thus ending the Tetrarchy. St Peter’s Church in Rome is founded.

326

326

君士坦丁一世建立了君士坦丁堡，并将拜占庭并入这座新城。

Constantine I founds Constantinople and incorporates Byzantium into the new city.

330

330

君士坦丁一世将罗马帝国的首都从罗马迁至拜占庭，即后来的君士坦丁堡。弗鲁门提乌斯主教开始将埃塞俄比亚-厄立特里亚的阿克苏姆王国皈依基督教。

Constantine I moves the capital of the Roman Empire from Rome to Byzantium, later known as Constantinople. Bishop Frumentius begins his conversion of the kingdom of Axum in Ethiopia-Eritrea to Christianity.

332

332

君士坦丁一世皇帝在战场上击败西哥特人；西哥特人成为罗马的盟友。

Emperor Constantine I defeats the Visigoths in battle; they become Roman allies.

337

337

君士坦丁一世之死。

The death of Constantine I.

340

340

君士坦丁的两个儿子，君士坦斯和君士坦提乌斯二世，瓜分了罗马帝国。

Constantine’s sons, Constans and Constantius II, split the Roman Empire between them.

349

349

蒙古人（原始蒙古人）控制了中国北方。

The Mou-jong (proto-Mongols) take control of the north of China.

350

350

君士坦斯皇帝被马格嫩提乌斯杀死，后者被拥立为帝。库什文明被阿克苏姆王国的入侵所摧毁。

Emperor Constans is killed by Magnentius, who is proclaimed emperor. Kushite civilization is brought down by invasion from the kingdom of Axum.

351

351

在印度，一种新的工艺使得从甘蔗中提取糖成为可能。

In India, a new process makes it possible to extract sugar from sugar cane.

352

352

日耳曼部落阿拉曼尼人和法兰克人击败了罗马军队，控制了摩泽尔河和莱茵河之间的 40 个城镇。

The Germanic tribes, the Alamanni and the Franks, defeat the Roman army, taking control of 40 towns between the Moselle and the Rhine.

353

353

君士坦提乌斯二世击败马格嫩提乌斯，成为罗马帝国唯一的皇帝。

Constantius II defeats Magnentius and becomes sole Roman Emperor.

356

356

在罗马帝国，崇拜非基督教偶像的行为被禁止，君士坦提乌斯二世下令关闭所有异教神庙。罗马第一座圣彼得大教堂开始动工。

The worship of non-Christian images is banned in the Roman Empire and Constantius II orders the closure of all pagan temples. Work begins on the first basilica of St Peter in Rome.

360

360

大约在同一时期：匈奴人从亚洲中部入侵欧洲；撒克逊人首次入侵英国。

Around this time: Early invasions of Europe by Huns from Central Asia; the first invasions of Britain by the Saxons.

361

361

尤利安成为罗马皇帝，并试图恢复异教信仰。中国哀帝继承了穆帝的王位。

Julian becomes Roman Emperor and tries to restore paganism. Emperor Ai succeeds Emperor Mu in China.

362

362

皇帝朱利安入侵波斯，但被迫撤退。

Emperor Julian invades Persia, but is forced to retreat.

363

363

朱利安率领九万大军进攻波斯，战死沙场。约维安被拥立为帝。匈奴人抵达里海。

Julian attacks Persia with an army of 90,000 men and is killed in the fighting. Jovian is declared Emperor. The Huns reach the Caspian Sea.

364

364

约维安将美索不达米亚割让给波斯人，不久后去世；瓦伦提尼安一世继位，瓦伦斯为共治皇帝。老底嘉会议决定了基督教教会的教义和《圣经》的内容。

Jovian surrenders Mesopotamia to the Persians and dies shortly after; Valentinian I becomes Emperor, with co-emperor Valens. The Council of Laodicea decides the doctirine of the Christian Church and the contents of the Bible.

365

365

秦始皇继秦哀皇之后成为中国皇帝。

Emperor Fei succeeds Emperor Ai in China.

366

366

阿拉曼尼人入侵罗马帝国。

The Alamanni invade the Roman Empire.

367

367

大阴谋：撒克逊人、爱尔兰人和阿塔科蒂人联合发动进攻，同时哈德良长城驻军起义，企图摧毁罗马不列颠。亚历山大的圣亚他那修是第一个列出新约27卷书的人。

The Great Conspiracy: an assault featuring Saxons, Irish and Attacotti combines with a revolt of the garrison on Hadrian’s Wall to devastate Roman Britain. St Athanasius of Alexandria is the first person to list the 27 books of the New Testament.

368

368

狄奥多西伯爵平息了不列颠的大阴谋。瓦伦提尼安在帝国边境的莱茵河畔击败了阿勒曼尼人。

Count Theodosius quashes the Great Conspiracy in Britain. Valentinian defeats the Alemanni along the Empire’s border, at the Rhine.

369

369

波斯国王沙普尔二世占领了亲罗马的亚美尼亚王国。

Shapur II, the Persian king, occupies the pro-Roman kingdom of Armenia.

370

370

东哥特人被匈奴人征服。匈奴人摧毁了阿兰帝国，并渡过伏尔加河和顿河。

The Ostrogoths are conquered by the Huns. The Huns destroy the empire of the Alans and cross the Volga and the Don.

372

372

瓦伦提尼安一世击败了日耳曼小部落夸迪人和萨尔马特人，并征服了非洲的摩尔人。中国皇帝飞帝被废黜，建文帝继位。孝武帝又继位建文帝。

Valentinian I defeats the small Germanic tribe, the Quadi, and the Sarmates and crushes the Moors in Africa. Emperor Fei of China is dethroned and replaced by Jianwen. Emperor Xiaowu, in turn, succeeds Jianwen.

374

374

投矛猫头鹰成为特奥蒂瓦坎的皇帝。

Spearthrower Owl becomes Emperor of Teotihuacan.

375

375

瓦伦提尼安一世去世。格拉提安和瓦伦提尼安二世继位为罗马皇帝。拉比阿什撰写了《巴比伦塔木德》，这部著作约有5894页，250万字。韩国首批两座佛教寺庙建成。

The death of Valentinian I. Gratian and Valentinian II become Roman Emperors. The Talmud of Babylon – approximately 2.5 million words on 5,894 pages – is written by Rav Ashi. The first two Korean Buddhist temples are built.

376

376

匈奴人抵达罗马边境。印度国王旃陀罗笈多二世统治时期开始。

The Huns arrive on the Roman frontier. The beginning of the reign of Chandragupta II, king of India.

377

377

波斯国王沙普尔二世将匈奴人击退至高加索山脉以北。中国画家顾恺之创作了《洛河女神图》。

Persian King Shapur II pushes the Huns back across the Caucasus. The Chinese painter Gu Kaizhi paints his work The Goddess of the Lo River.

378

378

西哥特人在阿德里安堡击败罗马人；皇帝瓦伦斯在战斗中阵亡。

The Visigoths defeat the Romans at Adrianople; Emperor Valens is killed in the battle.

379

379

尼尔成为爱尔兰国王。狄奥多西一世在锡尔米乌姆加冕为罗马皇帝；格拉提安拒绝接受东罗马皇帝的称号。阿尔达希尔二世成为波斯国王。

Niall becomes king of Ireland. Theodosius I becomes Roman Emperor at Sirmium; Gratianus refuses the title of Eastern Emperor. Ardeshir II becomes king of Persia.

380

380

狄奥多西一世宣布基督教为罗马帝国的国教。汪达尔人入侵罗马帝国。印度国王笈多吞并西部行省，从而控制了与欧洲和埃及的贸易。圣杰罗姆用拉丁文翻译的《圣经》通俗本《武加大译本》出版。

Theodosius I declares Christianity to be the official religion of the Roman Empire. The invasion of the Roman Empire by the Vandals. The annexation of the western provinces by Indian King Gupta gives him control over commerce with Europe and Egypt. The Vulgate, a translation in Latin of the Bible by St Jerome, is published.

382

382

狄奥多西一世与西哥特人缔结和平条约，允许他们在多瑙河南岸定居。阿拉里克一世成为西哥特国王。

Theodosius I concludes a peace treaty with the Visigoths, allowing them to settle south of the Danube. Alaric I becomes king of the Visigoths.

383

383

阿卡狄乌斯成为罗马皇帝；驻扎在不列颠的罗马军队拥立马格努斯·马克西姆斯为帝，高卢、意大利行省和西班牙也纷纷效仿。沙普尔三世成为波斯国王。在墨西哥，托尔特克人正在建造世界上最高的金字塔。在中国，在飞水之战中，晋朝击败了秦朝。

Arcadius becomes Emperor of Rome; Roman troops in Britain declare Magnus Maximus to be their emperor, as do Gaul, the Italian provinces and Hispania. Shapur III becomes king of Persia. In Mexico, the Toltecs are constructing the tallest pyramids on earth. In China, in the Battle of Feishui, the Jin dynasty defeats the former Qin dynasty.

384

384

朝鲜百济国王真柔称帝，宣布佛教为国教。

King Chimnyu becomes king of Baekje in Korea and declares Buddhism the official religion.

385

385

铜的开采和铸造始于非洲南部扎伊尔和赞比亚边境的坎桑希。

Copper extraction and casting begins in Kansanshi, on the border of Zaire and Zambia in southern Africa.

386

386

罗马皇帝狄奥多西一世与波斯媾和，瓜分亚美尼亚。马格努斯·马克西姆斯入侵意大利，驱逐瓦伦提尼安二世，后者投奔狄奥多西一世避难。圣奥古斯丁皈依基督教。中国北魏王朝建立。中国南北分裂时期（直至589年）。

Theodosius I of Rome makes peace with Persia; they divide Armenia between them. Magnus Maximus invades Italy, driving out Valentinian II, who takes refuge with Theodosius. The conversion of St Augustine. The beginning of the Northern Wei Dynasty in China. A period of division between the north and the south of China (until 589).

387

387

爱尔兰守护圣人圣帕特里克诞辰。

The birth of St Patrick, patron saint of Ireland.

388

388

马格努斯·马克西姆斯在萨维战役中战败，瓦伦提尼安二世复辟为西罗马皇帝。巴赫拉姆四世成为波斯国王。

Magnus Maximus is defeated at the Battle of the Save, and Valentinian II is restored as Western Roman Emperor. Bahram IV becomes king of Persia.

389

389

亚历山大城的异教建筑，包括图书馆，在狄奥多西的命令下被摧毁。

Pagan buildings in Alexandria, including the library, are destroyed on the order of Theodosius.

390

390

卢德拉塞纳 (Rudrasena) 成为印度德干高原瓦卡塔卡 (Vakataka) 的皇帝。 《爱经》由瓦齐耶那修订。

Rudrasena becomes emperor of Vakataka in the Deccan Plateau of India. The Kama Sutra is revised by Vatsyayana.

391

391

狄奥多西一世将基督教确立为罗马帝国的国教，禁止崇拜其他神灵。

Theodosius establishes Christianity as the official state religion of the Roman Empire, making the worship of other gods illegal.

392

392

法兰克将军阿尔博加斯特刺杀瓦伦提尼安二世后，提名尤金尼乌斯为西罗马帝国皇帝。

Arbogast, a Frankish general, nominates Eugenius as Emperor of the Western Roman Empire, after assassinating Valentinian II.

393

393

狄奥多西一世皇帝下令禁止奥林匹克运动会；这项运动会已经举办了1000年。高祖继承太祖成为后秦皇帝。

Emperor Theodosius I outlaws the Olympic Games; they have been held for 1,000 years. Gao Zu succeeds Tai Zu as Emperor of the Later Qin Empire in China.

394

394

狄奥多西一世皇帝在弗里吉杜斯河战役中击败并杀死了尤金尼乌斯和阿尔博加斯特。

Emperor Theodosius I defeats and kills Eugenius and Arbogast at the Battle of the Frigidus.

395

395

狄奥多西一世驾崩；帝国分裂为东西两部分。阿卡狄乌斯成为东罗马皇帝，霍诺留斯成为西罗马皇帝。西哥特国王阿拉里克向罗马帝国宣战。圣奥古斯丁成为希波主教。

The death of Theodosius I; the empire is divided into East and West. Arcadius becomes Eastern Emperor; Honorius becomes Western Emperor. Alaric, the Visigoth king, goes to war against the Roman Empire. St Augustine becomes Bishop of Hippo Regius.

396

396

罗马人征召法兰克人和阿勒曼尼人守卫莱茵河边境。匈奴人占领了罗马尼亚潘诺尼亚平原。埃琉西斯秘仪终结，阿拉里克一世摧毁了希腊的古代遗址。金安帝继承孝武帝的王位，成为中国晋朝的统治者。
